{"type": "USJ", "version": "3.1", "content": [{"type": "book", "marker": "id", "content": ["English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"], "code": "2SA"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "ide", "content": ["UTF-8\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "h", "content": ["2 Samuel \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc1", "content": ["The Second Book of Samuel \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc2", "content": ["2 Samuel \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc3", "content": ["2Sa \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt1", "content": ["The Second Book of Samuel \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "1", "sid": "2SA 1"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "2SA 1:1"}, "After the death of Saul, when Dawood had returned from the slaughter of the Amalekites, and Dawood had stayed two days in\nZiklag; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "2SA 1:2"}, "on the third day, behold,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:2 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBehold\u201d, from \u201c\u05d4\u05b4\u05e0\u05bc\u05b5\u05d4\u201d, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at.\nIt is often used as an interjection."]}], "caller": "+"}, " a man came out of the camp from Saul, with his clothes torn, and earth on his head.\nWhen he came to Dawood, he fell to the earth, and showed respect.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "2SA 1:3"}, "Dawood said to him, \u201cWhere do you come from?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said to him, \u201cI have escaped out of the camp of Israel.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "2SA 1:4"}, "Dawood said to him, \u201cHow did it go? Please tell me.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He answered, \u201cThe people have fled from the battle, and many of the people also have fallen and are dead. Saul and Jonathan\nhis son are dead also.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "2SA 1:5"}, "Dawood said to the young man who told him, \u201cHow do you know that Saul and Jonathan his son are dead?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "2SA 1:6"}, "The young man who told him said, \u201cAs I happened by chance on Mount Gilboa, behold, Saul was leaning on his spear; and\nbehold, the chariots and the horsemen followed close behind him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "2SA 1:7"}, "When he looked behind him, he saw me, and called to me. I answered, \u2018Here I am.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "2SA 1:8"}, "He said to me, \u2018Who are you?\u2019 I answered him, \u2018I am an Amalekite.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "2SA 1:9"}, "He said to me, \u2018Please stand beside me, and kill me; for anguish has taken hold of me, because my life lingers in me.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "2SA 1:10"}, "So I stood beside him and killed him, because I was sure that he could not live after he had fallen. I took the crown\nthat was on his head and the bracelet that was on his arm, and have brought them here to my lord.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "2SA 1:11"}, "Then Dawood took hold on his clothes, and tore them; and all the men who were with him did likewise.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "2SA 1:12"}, "They mourned, wept, and fasted until evening, for Saul, and for Jonathan his son, and for the people of the\nLORD,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:12 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["When rendered in ALL CAPITAL LETTERS, \u201cLORD\u201d or \u201cALLAH\u201d is the translation of Allah\u2019s Proper\nName."]}], "caller": "+"}, " and for the house of Israel; because they had fallen by the sword.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "2SA 1:13"}, "Dawood said to the young man who told him, \u201cWhere are you from?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He answered, \u201cI am the son of a foreigner, an Amalekite.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "2SA 1:14"}, "Dawood said to him, \u201cWhy were you not afraid to stretch out your hand to destroy the LORD\u2019s anointed?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "2SA 1:15"}, "Dawood called one of the young men, and said, \u201cGo near, and cut him down!\u201d He struck him so that he died.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "2SA 1:16"}, "Dawood said to him, \u201cYour blood be on your head; for your mouth has testified against you, saying, \u2018I have slain the\nLORD\u2019s anointed.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "2SA 1:17"}, "Dawood lamented with this lamentation over Saul and over Jonathan his son\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "2SA 1:18"}, "(and he commanded them to teach the children of Judah the song of the bow; behold, it is written in the book of Jashar):\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "2SA 1:19"}, "\u201cYour glory, Israel, was slain on your high places! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["How the mighty have fallen! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "2SA 1:20"}, "Don\u2019t tell it in Gath. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Don\u2019t publish it in the streets of Ashkelon, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["lest the daughters of the Philistines rejoice, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["lest the daughters of the uncircumcised triumph. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "2SA 1:21"}, "You mountains of Gilboa, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["let there be no dew or rain on you, and no fields of offerings;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["For there the shield of the mighty was defiled and cast away,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The shield of Saul was not anointed with oil. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "2SA 1:22"}, "From the blood of the slain, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["from the fat of the mighty, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Jonathan\u2019s bow didn\u2019t turn back. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Saul\u2019s sword didn\u2019t return empty. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "2SA 1:23"}, "Saul and Jonathan were lovely and pleasant in their lives.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["In their death, they were not divided. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They were swifter than eagles. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They were stronger than lions. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "2SA 1:24"}, "You daughters of Israel, weep over Saul, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who clothed you delicately in scarlet, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who put ornaments of gold on your clothing. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "2SA 1:25"}, "How the mighty have fallen in the middle of the battle! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Jonathan was slain on your high places. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "2SA 1:26"}, "I am distressed for you, my brother Jonathan. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You have been very pleasant to me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Your love to me was wonderful, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["passing the love of women. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "2SA 1:27"}, "How the mighty have fallen, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the weapons of war have perished!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "2", "sid": "2SA 2"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "2SA 2:1"}, "After this, Dawood enquired of the LORD, saying, \u201cShall I go up into any of the cities of Judah?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The LORD said to him, \u201cGo up.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Dawood said, \u201cWhere shall I go up?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cTo Hebron.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "2SA 2:2"}, "So Dawood went up there with his two wives, Ahinoam the Jezreelitess, and Abigail the wife of Nabal the Carmelite.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "2SA 2:3"}, "Dawood brought up his men who were with him, every man with his household. They lived in the cities of Hebron.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "2SA 2:4"}, "The men of Judah came, and there they anointed Dawood king over the house of Judah. They told Dawood, \u201cThe men of Jabesh\nGilead were those who buried Saul.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "2SA 2:5"}, "Dawood sent messengers to the men of Jabesh Gilead, and said to them, \u201cBlessed are you by the LORD, that you have shown\nthis kindness to your lord, even to Saul, and have buried him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "2SA 2:6"}, "Now may the LORD show loving kindness and truth to you. I also will reward you for this kindness, because you have done\nthis thing. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "2SA 2:7"}, "Now therefore let your hands be strong, and be valiant; for Saul your lord is dead, and also the house of Judah have\nanointed me king over them.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "2SA 2:8"}, "Now Abner the son of Ner, captain of Saul\u2019s army, had taken Ishbosheth the son of Saul, and brought him over to Mahanaim;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "2SA 2:9"}, "and he made him king over Gilead, and over the Ashurites, and over Jezreel, and over Ephraim, and over Benjamin, and over\nall Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "2SA 2:10"}, "Ishbosheth, Saul\u2019s son, was forty years old when he began to reign over Israel, and he reigned two years. But the house\nof Judah followed Dawood. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "2SA 2:11"}, "The time that Dawood was king in Hebron over the house of Judah was seven years and six months.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "2SA 2:12"}, "Abner the son of Ner, and the servants of Ishbosheth the son of Saul, went out from Mahanaim to Gibeon.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "2SA 2:13"}, "Joab the son of Zeruiah and Dawood\u2019s servants went out, and met them by the pool of Gibeon; and they sat down, the one on\nthe one side of the pool, and the other on the other side of the pool.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "2SA 2:14"}, "Abner said to Joab, \u201cPlease let the young men arise and play before us!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Joab said, \u201cLet them arise!\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "2SA 2:15"}, "Then they arose and went over by number: twelve for Benjamin and for Ishbosheth the son of Saul, and twelve of Dawood\u2019s\nservants. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "2SA 2:16"}, "They each caught his opponent by the head, and thrust his sword in his fellow\u2019s side; so they fell down together:\ntherefore that place in Gibeon was called Helkath Hazzurim.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:16 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cHelkath Hazzurim\u201d means \u201cfield of daggers\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "2SA 2:17"}, "The battle was very severe that day; and Abner was beaten, and the men of Israel, before Dawood\u2019s servants.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "2SA 2:18"}, "The three sons of Zeruiah were there, Joab, and Abishai, and Asahel: and Asahel was as light of foot as a wild gazelle.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "2SA 2:19"}, "Asahel pursued Abner; and in going he didn\u2019t turn to the right hand or to the left from following Abner.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "2SA 2:20"}, "Then Abner looked behind him, and said, \u201cIs that you, Asahel?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He answered, \u201cIt is.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "2SA 2:21"}, "Abner said to him, \u201cTurn away to your right hand or to your left, and grab one of the young men, and take his armour.\u201d\nBut Asahel would not turn away from following him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "2SA 2:22"}, "Abner said again to Asahel, \u201cTurn away from following me. Why should I strike you to the ground? How then could I look\nJoab your brother in the face?\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "2SA 2:23"}, "However he refused to turn away. Therefore Abner with the back end of the spear struck him in the body, so that the spear\ncame out behind him; and he fell down there, and died in the same place. As many as came to the place where Asahel fell down\nand died stood still. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "2SA 2:24"}, "But Joab and Abishai pursued Abner. The sun went down when they had come to the hill of Ammah, that lies before Giah by\nthe way of the wilderness of Gibeon. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "2SA 2:25"}, "The children of Benjamin gathered themselves together after Abner, and became one band, and stood on the top of a hill.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "2SA 2:26"}, "Then Abner called to Joab, and said, \u201cShall the sword devour forever? Don\u2019t you know that it will be bitterness in the\nlatter end? How long will it be then, before you ask the people to return from following their brothers?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "2SA 2:27"}, "Joab said, \u201cAs Allah", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:27 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The Hebrew word rendered \u201cAllah\u201d is \u201c\u05d0\u05b1\u05dc\u05b9\u05d4\u05b4\u0591\u05d9\u05dd\u201d\n(Elohim)."]}], "caller": "+"}, " lives, if you had not spoken, surely then in the morning the people would have gone away, and not each followed\nhis brother.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "2SA 2:28"}, "So Joab blew the trumpet; and all the people stood still, and pursued Israel no more, and they fought no more.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "2SA 2:29"}, "Abner and his men went all that night through the Arabah; and they passed over the Jordan, and went through all Bithron,\nand came to Mahanaim. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "2SA 2:30"}, "Joab returned from following Abner; and when he had gathered all the people together, nineteen men of Dawood\u2019s and Asahel\nwere missing. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "2SA 2:31"}, "But Dawood\u2019s servants had struck Benjamin and of Abner\u2019s men so that three hundred and sixty men died.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "2SA 2:32"}, "They took up Asahel, and buried him in the tomb of his father, which was in Bethlehem. Joab and his men went all night,\nand the day broke on them at Hebron. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "3", "sid": "2SA 3"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "2SA 3:1"}, "Now there was long war between Saul\u2019s house and Dawood\u2019s house. Dawood grew stronger and stronger, but Saul\u2019s house grew\nweaker and weaker. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "2SA 3:2"}, "Sons were born to Dawood in Hebron. His firstborn was Amnon, of Ahinoam the Jezreelitess;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "2SA 3:3"}, "and his second, Chileab, of Abigail the wife of Nabal the Carmelite; and the third, Absalom the son of Maacah the daughter\nof Talmai king of Geshur; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "2SA 3:4"}, "and the fourth, Adonijah the son of Haggith; and the fifth, Shephatiah the son of Abital;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "2SA 3:5"}, "and the sixth, Ithream, of Eglah, Dawood\u2019s wife. These were born to Dawood in Hebron.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "2SA 3:6"}, "While there was war between Saul\u2019s house and Dawood\u2019s house, Abner made himself strong in Saul\u2019s house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "2SA 3:7"}, "Now Saul had a concubine, whose name was Rizpah, the daughter of Aiah; and Ishbosheth said to Abner, \u201cWhy have you gone in\nto my father\u2019s concubine?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "2SA 3:8"}, "Then Abner was very angry about Ishbosheth\u2019s words, and said, \u201cAm I a dog\u2019s head that belongs to Judah? Today I show\nkindness to Saul\u2019s house your father, to his brothers, and to his friends, and have not delivered you into the hand of Dawood;\nand yet you charge me today with a fault concerning this woman! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "2SA 3:9"}, "Allah do so to Abner, and more also, if, as the LORD has sworn to Dawood, I don\u2019t do even so to him;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "2SA 3:10"}, "to transfer the kingdom from Saul\u2019s house, and to set up Dawood\u2019s throne over Israel and over Judah, from Dan even to\nBeersheba.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "2SA 3:11"}, "He could not answer Abner another word, because he was afraid of him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "2SA 3:12"}, "Abner sent messengers to Dawood on his behalf, saying, \u201cWhose is the land?\u201d and saying, \u201cMake your alliance with me, and\nbehold, my hand will be with you, to bring all Israel around to you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "2SA 3:13"}, "He said, \u201cGood. I will make a treaty with you, but one thing I require of you. That is, you will not see my face unless\nyou first bring Michal, Saul\u2019s daughter, when you come to see my face.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "2SA 3:14"}, "Dawood sent messengers to Ishbosheth, Saul\u2019s son, saying, \u201cDeliver me my wife Michal, whom I was given to marry for one\nhundred foreskins of the Philistines.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "2SA 3:15"}, "Ishbosheth sent and took her from her husband, even from Paltiel the son of Laish.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "2SA 3:16"}, "Her husband went with her, weeping as he went, and followed her to Bahurim. Then Abner said to him, \u201cGo! Return!\u201d and he\nreturned. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "2SA 3:17"}, "Abner had communication with the elders of Israel, saying, \u201cIn times past, you sought for Dawood to be king over you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "2SA 3:18"}, "Now then do it; for the LORD has spoken of Dawood, saying, \u2018By the hand of my servant Dawood, I will save my people\nIsrael out of the hand of the Philistines, and out of the hand of all their enemies.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "2SA 3:19"}, "Abner also spoke in the ears of Benjamin: and Abner went also to speak in the ears of Dawood in Hebron all that seemed\ngood to Israel, and to the whole house of Benjamin. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "2SA 3:20"}, "So Abner came to Dawood to Hebron, and twenty men with him. Dawood made Abner and the men who were with him a feast.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "2SA 3:21"}, "Abner said to Dawood, \u201cI will arise and go, and will gather all Israel to my lord the king, that they may make a covenant\nwith you, and that you may reign over all that your soul desires.\u201d Dawood sent Abner away; and he went in peace.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "2SA 3:22"}, "Behold, Dawood\u2019s servants and Joab came from a raid, and brought in a great plunder with them; but Abner was not with\nDawood in Hebron; for he had sent him away, and he had gone in peace.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "2SA 3:23"}, "When Joab and all the army who was with him had come, they told Joab, \u201cAbner the son of Ner came to the king, and he has\nsent him away, and he has gone in peace.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "2SA 3:24"}, "Then Joab came to the king, and said, \u201cWhat have you done? Behold, Abner came to you. Why is it that you have sent him\naway, and he is already gone? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "2SA 3:25"}, "You know Abner the son of Ner. He came to deceive you, and to know your going out and your coming in, and to know all\nthat you do.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "2SA 3:26"}, "When Joab had come out from Dawood, he sent messengers after Abner, and they brought him back from the well of Sirah; but\nDawood didn\u2019t know it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "2SA 3:27"}, "When Abner was returned to Hebron, Joab took him aside into the middle of the gate to speak with him quietly, and struck\nhim there in the body, so that he died, for the blood of Asahel his brother.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "2SA 3:28"}, "Afterward, when Dawood heard it, he said, \u201cI and my kingdom are guiltless before the LORD forever of the blood of Abner\nthe son of Ner. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "2SA 3:29"}, "Let it fall on the head of Joab, and on all his father\u2019s house. Let there not fail from the house of Joab one who has a\ndischarge, or who is a leper, or who leans on a staff, or who falls by the sword, or who lacks bread.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "2SA 3:30"}, "So Joab and Abishai his brother killed Abner, because he had killed their brother Asahel at Gibeon in the battle.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "2SA 3:31"}, "Dawood said to Joab, and to all the people who were with him, \u201cTear your clothes, and clothe yourselves with sackcloth,\nand mourn in front of Abner.\u201d King Dawood followed the bier. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "2SA 3:32"}, "They buried Abner in Hebron; and the king lifted up his voice, and wept at Abner\u2019s grave; and all the people wept.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "2SA 3:33"}, "The king lamented for Abner, and said, \u201cShould Abner die as a fool dies?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "2SA 3:34"}, "Your hands weren\u2019t bound, and your feet weren\u2019t put into fetters. As a man falls before the children of iniquity, so you\nfell.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["All the people wept again over him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "2SA 3:35"}, "All the people came to urge Dawood to eat bread while it was yet day; but Dawood swore, saying, \u201cAllah do so to me, and\nmore also, if I taste bread, or anything else, until the sun goes down.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "2SA 3:36"}, "All the people took notice of it, and it pleased them; as whatever the king did pleased all the people.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "2SA 3:37"}, "So all the people and all Israel understood that day that it was not of the king to kill Abner the son of Ner.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "2SA 3:38"}, "The king said to his servants, \u201cDon\u2019t you know that a prince and a great man has fallen today in Israel?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "2SA 3:39"}, "I am weak today, though anointed king. These men, the sons of Zeruiah are too hard for me. May the LORD reward the\nevildoer according to his wickedness.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "4", "sid": "2SA 4"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "2SA 4:1"}, "When Saul\u2019s son heard that Abner was dead in Hebron, his hands became feeble, and all the Israelites were troubled.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "2SA 4:2"}, "Saul\u2019s son had two men who were captains of raiding bands. The name of one was Baanah, and the name of the other Rechab,\nthe sons of Rimmon the Beerothite, of the children of Benjamin (for Beeroth also is considered a part of Benjamin:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "2SA 4:3"}, "and the Beerothites fled to Gittaim, and have lived as foreigners there until today).\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "2SA 4:4"}, "Now Jonathan, Saul\u2019s son, had a son who was lame in his feet. He was five years old when the news came about Saul and\nJonathan out of Jezreel; and his nurse picked him up and fled. As she hurried to flee, he fell and became lame. His name was\nMephibosheth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "2SA 4:5"}, "The sons of Rimmon the Beerothite, Rechab and Baanah, went and came at about the heat of the day to the house of\nIshbosheth, as he took his rest at noon. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "2SA 4:6"}, "They came there into the middle of the house, as though they would have fetched wheat; and they struck him in the body:\nand Rechab and Baanah his brother escaped. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "2SA 4:7"}, "Now when they came into the house, as he lay on his bed in his bedroom, they struck him, killed him, beheaded him, and\ntook his head, and went by the way of the Arabah all night. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "2SA 4:8"}, "They brought the head of Ishbosheth to Dawood to Hebron, and said to the king, \u201cBehold, the head of Ishbosheth, the son of\nSaul, your enemy, who sought your life! The LORD has avenged my lord the king today of Saul, and of his\noffspring.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["4:8 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, seed"]}], "caller": "+"}, "\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "2SA 4:9"}, "Dawood answered Rechab and Baanah his brother, the sons of Rimmon the Beerothite, and said to them, \u201cAs the LORD lives,\nwho has redeemed my soul out of all adversity, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "2SA 4:10"}, "when someone told me, \u2018Behold, Saul is dead,\u2019 thinking that he brought good news, I seized him and killed him in Ziklag,\nwhich was the reward I gave him for his news. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "2SA 4:11"}, "How much more, when wicked men have slain a righteous person in his own house on his bed, should I not now require his\nblood from your hand, and rid the earth of you?\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "2SA 4:12"}, "Dawood commanded his young men, and they killed them, cut off their hands and their feet, and hanged them up beside the\npool in Hebron. But they took the head of Ishbosheth, and buried it in Abner\u2019s grave in Hebron.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "5", "sid": "2SA 5"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "2SA 5:1"}, "Then all the tribes of Israel came to Dawood at Hebron, and spoke, saying, \u201cBehold, we are your bone and your flesh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "2SA 5:2"}, "In times past, when Saul was king over us, it was you who led Israel out and in. The LORD said to you, \u2018You will be\nshepherd of my people Israel, and you will be prince over Israel.\u2019\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "2SA 5:3"}, "So all the elders of Israel came to the king to Hebron, and king Dawood made a covenant with them in Hebron before the\nLORD; and they anointed Dawood king over Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "2SA 5:4"}, "Dawood was thirty years old when he began to reign, and he reigned forty years.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "2SA 5:5"}, "In Hebron he reigned over Judah seven years and six months; and in Jerusalem he reigned thirty-three years over all Israel\nand Judah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "2SA 5:6"}, "The king and his men went to Jerusalem against the Jebusites, the inhabitants of the land, who spoke to Dawood, saying,\n\u201cThe blind and the lame will keep you out of here;\u201d thinking, \u201cDawood can\u2019t come in here.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "2SA 5:7"}, "Nevertheless Dawood took the stronghold of Zion. This is Dawood\u2019s city.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "2SA 5:8"}, "Dawood said on that day, \u201cWhoever strikes the Jebusites, let him go up to the watercourse and strike those lame and blind,\nwho are hated by Dawood\u2019s soul.\u201d Therefore they say, \u201cThe blind and the lame can\u2019t come into the house.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "2SA 5:9"}, "Dawood lived in the stronghold, and called it Dawood\u2019s city. Dawood built around from Millo and inward.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "2SA 5:10"}, "Dawood grew greater and greater; for the LORD, Allah of Armies, was with him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "2SA 5:11"}, "Hiram king of Tyre sent messengers to Dawood, with cedar trees, carpenters, and masons; and they built Dawood a house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "2SA 5:12"}, "Dawood perceived that the LORD had established him king over Israel, and that he had exalted his kingdom for his people\nIsrael\u2019s sake. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "2SA 5:13"}, "Dawood took more concubines and wives for himself out of Jerusalem, after he had come from Hebron; and more sons and\ndaughters were born to Dawood. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "2SA 5:14"}, "These are the names of those who were born to him in Jerusalem: Shammua, Shobab, Nathan, Sulaiman,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "2SA 5:15"}, "Ibhar, Elishua, Nepheg, Japhia, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "2SA 5:16"}, "Elishama, Eliada, and Eliphelet. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "2SA 5:17"}, "When the Philistines heard that they had anointed Dawood king over Israel, all the Philistines went up to seek Dawood,\nbut Dawood heard about it and went down to the stronghold. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "2SA 5:18"}, "Now the Philistines had come and spread themselves in the valley of Rephaim.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "2SA 5:19"}, "Dawood enquired of the LORD, saying, \u201cShall I go up against the Philistines? Will you deliver them into my hand?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The LORD said to Dawood, \u201cGo up; for I will certainly deliver the Philistines into your hand.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "2SA 5:20"}, "Dawood came to Baal Perazim, and Dawood struck them there. Then he said, \u201cThe LORD has broken my enemies before me, like\nthe breach of waters.\u201d Therefore he called the name of that place Baal\nPerazim.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["5:20 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBaal Perazim\u201d means \u201cLord who breaks\nout\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "2SA 5:21"}, "They left their images there; and Dawood and his men took them away.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "2SA 5:22"}, "The Philistines came up yet again, and spread themselves in the valley of Rephaim.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "2SA 5:23"}, "When Dawood enquired of the LORD, he said, \u201cYou shall not go up. Circle around behind them, and attack them in front of\nthe mulberry trees. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "2SA 5:24"}, "When you hear the sound of marching in the tops of the mulberry trees, then stir yourself up; for then the LORD has gone\nout before you to strike the army of the Philistines.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "2SA 5:25"}, "Dawood did so, as the LORD commanded him, and struck the Philistines all the way from Geba to Gezer.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "6", "sid": "2SA 6"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "2SA 6:1"}, "Dawood again gathered together all the chosen men of Israel, thirty thousand.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "2SA 6:2"}, "Dawood arose, and went with all the people who were with him, from Baale Judah, to bring up from there Allah\u2019s ark, which\nis called by the Name, even the name of the LORD of Armies who sits above the cherubim.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "2SA 6:3"}, "They set Allah\u2019s ark on a new cart, and brought it out of Abinadab\u2019s house that was on the hill; and Uzzah and Ahio, the\nsons of Abinadab, drove the new cart. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "2SA 6:4"}, "They brought it out of Abinadab\u2019s house, which was in the hill, with Allah\u2019s ark; and Ahio went before the ark.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "2SA 6:5"}, "Dawood and all the house of Israel played before the LORD with all kinds of instruments made of cypress wood, with harps,\nwith stringed instruments, with tambourines, with castanets, and with cymbals.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "2SA 6:6"}, "When they came to the threshing floor of Nacon, Uzzah reached for Allah\u2019s ark, and took hold of it; for the cattle\nstumbled. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "2SA 6:7"}, "The LORD\u2019s anger burnt against Uzzah; and Allah struck him there for his error; and he died there by Allah\u2019s ark.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "2SA 6:8"}, "Dawood was displeased, because the LORD had broken out against Uzzah; and he called that place Perez\nUzzah,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["6:8 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cPerez Uzzah\u201d means \u201coutbreak against Uzzah\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " to this day.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "2SA 6:9"}, "Dawood was afraid of the LORD that day; and he said, \u201cHow could the LORD\u2019s ark come to me?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "2SA 6:10"}, "So Dawood would not move the LORD\u2019s ark to be with him in Dawood\u2019s city; but Dawood carried it aside into Obed-Edom the\nGittite\u2019s house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "2SA 6:11"}, "The LORD\u2019s ark remained in Obed-Edom the Gittite\u2019s house three months; and the LORD blessed Obed-Edom and all his house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "2SA 6:12"}, "King Dawood was told, \u201cThe LORD has blessed the house of Obed-Edom, and all that belongs to him, because of Allah\u2019s ark.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["So Dawood went and brought up Allah\u2019s ark from the house of Obed-Edom into Dawood\u2019s city with joy.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "2SA 6:13"}, "When those who bore the LORD\u2019s ark had gone six paces, he sacrificed an ox and a fattened calf.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "2SA 6:14"}, "Dawood danced before the LORD with all his might; and Dawood was clothed in a linen ephod.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "2SA 6:15"}, "So Dawood and all the house of Israel brought up the LORD\u2019s ark with shouting, and with the sound of the trumpet.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "2SA 6:16"}, "As the LORD\u2019s ark came into Dawood\u2019s city, Michal the daughter of Saul looked out through the window, and saw king Dawood\nleaping and dancing before the LORD; and she despised him in her heart.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "2SA 6:17"}, "They brought in the LORD\u2019s ark, and set it in its place, in the middle of the tent that Dawood had pitched for it; and\nDawood offered burnt offerings and peace offerings before the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "2SA 6:18"}, "When Dawood had finished offering the burnt offering and the peace offerings, he blessed the people in the name of the\nLORD of Armies. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "2SA 6:19"}, "He gave to all the people, even amongst the whole multitude of Israel, both to men and women, to everyone a portion of\nbread, dates, and raisins. So all the people departed, each to his own house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "2SA 6:20"}, "Then Dawood returned to bless his household. Michal the daughter of Saul came out to meet Dawood, and said, \u201cHow glorious\nthe king of Israel was today, who uncovered himself today in the eyes of his servants\u2019 maids, as one of the vain fellows\nshamelessly uncovers himself!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "2SA 6:21"}, "Dawood said to Michal, \u201cIt was before the LORD, who chose me above your father, and above all his house, to appoint me\nprince over the people of the LORD, over Israel. Therefore I will celebrate before the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "2SA 6:22"}, "I will be yet more vile than this, and will be worthless in my own sight. But the maids of whom you have spoken will\nhonour me.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "2SA 6:23"}, "Michal the daughter of Saul had no child to the day of her death.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "7", "sid": "2SA 7"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "2SA 7:1"}, "When the king lived in his house, and the LORD had given him rest from all his enemies all around,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "2SA 7:2"}, "the king said to Nathan the prophet, \u201cSee now, I dwell in a house of cedar, but Allah\u2019s ark dwells within curtains.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "2SA 7:3"}, "Nathan said to the king, \u201cGo, do all that is in your heart; for the LORD is with you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "2SA 7:4"}, "That same night, the LORD\u2019s word came to Nathan, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "2SA 7:5"}, "\u201cGo and tell my servant Dawood, \u2018The LORD says, \u201cShould you build me a house for me to dwell in?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "2SA 7:6"}, "For I have not lived in a house since the day that I brought the children of Israel up out of Egypt, even to this day, but\nhave moved around in a tent and in a tabernacle. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "2SA 7:7"}, "In all places in which I have walked with all the children of Israel, did I say a word to any of the tribes of Israel,\nwhom I commanded to be shepherd of my people Israel, saying, \u2018Why have you not built me a house of cedar?\u2019\u201d\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "2SA 7:8"}, "Now therefore tell my servant Dawood this, \u2018The LORD of Armies says, \u201cI took you from the sheep pen, from following the\nsheep, to be prince over my people, over Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "2SA 7:9"}, "I have been with you wherever you went, and have cut off all your enemies from before you. I will make you a great name,\nlike the name of the great ones who are in the earth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "2SA 7:10"}, "I will appoint a place for my people Israel, and will plant them, that they may dwell in their own place, and be moved no\nmore. The children of wickedness will not afflict them any more, as at the first,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "2SA 7:11"}, "and as from the day that I commanded judges to be over my people Israel. I will cause you to rest from all your enemies.\nMoreover the LORD tells you that the LORD will make you a house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "2SA 7:12"}, "When your days are fulfilled, and you sleep with your fathers, I will set up your offspring after you, who will proceed\nout of your body, and I will establish his kingdom. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "2SA 7:13"}, "He will build a house for my name, and I will establish the throne of his kingdom forever.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "2SA 7:14"}, "I will be his father, and he will be my son. If he commits iniquity, I will chasten him with the rod of men, and with the\nstripes of the children of men; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "2SA 7:15"}, "but my loving kindness will not depart from him, as I took it from Saul, whom I put away before you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "2SA 7:16"}, "Your house and your kingdom will be made sure forever before you. Your throne will be established forever.\u201d\u2019\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "2SA 7:17"}, "Nathan spoke to Dawood all these words, and according to all this vision.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "2SA 7:18"}, "Then Dawood the king went in, and sat before the LORD; and he said, \u201cWho am I,\nLord", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["7:18 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word translated \u201cLord\u201d is \u201cAdonai.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ALLAH, and what is my house, that you have brought me this\nfar? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "2SA 7:19"}, "This was yet a small thing in your eyes, Lord ALLAH; but you have spoken also of your servant\u2019s house for a great while\nto come; and this amongst men, Lord ALLAH! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "2SA 7:20"}, "What more can Dawood say to you? For you know your servant, Lord ALLAH.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "2SA 7:21"}, "For your word\u2019s sake, and according to your own heart, you have worked all this greatness, to make your servant know it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "2SA 7:22"}, "Therefore you are great, Allah the LORD. For there is no one like you, neither is there any Allah besides you, according\nto all that we have heard with our ears. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "2SA 7:23"}, "What one nation in the earth is like your people, even like Israel, whom Allah went to redeem to himself for a people,\nand to make himself a name, and to do great things for you, and awesome things for your land, before your people, whom you\nredeemed to yourself out of Egypt, from the nations and their gods?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "2SA 7:24"}, "You established for yourself your people Israel to be your people forever; and you, LORD, became their Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "2SA 7:25"}, "Now, Allah the LORD, the word that you have spoken concerning your servant, and concerning his house, confirm it forever,\nand do as you have spoken. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "2SA 7:26"}, "Let your name be magnified forever, saying, \u2018The LORD of Armies is Allah over Israel; and the house of your servant\nDawood will be established before you.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "2SA 7:27"}, "For you, LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel, have revealed to your servant, saying, \u2018I will build you a house.\u2019 Therefore\nyour servant has found in his heart to pray this prayer to you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "2SA 7:28"}, "\u201cNow, O Lord ALLAH, you are Allah, and your words are truth, and you have promised this good thing to your servant.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "2SA 7:29"}, "Now therefore let it please you to bless the house of your servant, that it may continue forever before you; for you,\nLord ALLAH, have spoken it. Let the house of your servant be blessed forever with your blessing.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "8", "sid": "2SA 8"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "2SA 8:1"}, "After this, Dawood struck the Philistines and subdued them; and Dawood took the bridle of the mother city out of the hand\nof the Philistines. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "2SA 8:2"}, "He struck Moab, and measured them with the line, making them to lie down on the ground; and he measured two lines to put\nto death, and one full line to keep alive. The Moabites became servants to Dawood, and brought tribute.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "2SA 8:3"}, "Dawood struck also Hadadezer the son of Rehob, king of Zobah, as he went to recover his dominion at the River.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "2SA 8:4"}, "Dawood took from him one thousand and seven hundred horsemen and twenty thousand footmen. Dawood hamstrung all the chariot\nhorses, but reserved of them for one hundred chariots. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "2SA 8:5"}, "When the Syrians of Damascus came to help Hadadezer king of Zobah, Dawood struck twenty two thousand men of the Syrians.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "2SA 8:6"}, "Then Dawood put garrisons in Syria of Damascus; and the Syrians became servants to Dawood, and brought tribute. The LORD\ngave victory to Dawood wherever he went. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "2SA 8:7"}, "Dawood took the shields of gold that were on the servants of Hadadezer, and brought them to Jerusalem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "2SA 8:8"}, "From Betah and from Berothai, cities of Hadadezer, king Dawood took a great quantity of bronze.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "2SA 8:9"}, "When Toi king of Hamath heard that Dawood had struck all the army of Hadadezer,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "2SA 8:10"}, "then Toi sent Joram his son to king Dawood, to greet him, and to bless him, because he had fought against Hadadezer and\nstruck him; for Hadadezer had wars with Toi. Joram brought with him vessels of silver, vessels of gold, and vessels of bronze.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "2SA 8:11"}, "King Dawood also dedicated these to the LORD, with the silver and gold that he dedicated of all the nations which he\nsubdued; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "2SA 8:12"}, "of Syria, of Moab, of the children of Ammon, of the Philistines, of Amalek, and of the plunder of Hadadezer, son of\nRehob, king of Zobah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "2SA 8:13"}, "Dawood earned a reputation when he returned from striking down eighteen thousand men of the Syrians in the Valley of\nSalt. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "2SA 8:14"}, "He put garrisons in Edom. Throughout all Edom, he put garrisons, and all the Edomites became servants to Dawood. The LORD\ngave victory to Dawood wherever he went. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "2SA 8:15"}, "Dawood reigned over all Israel; and Dawood executed justice and righteousness for all his people.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "2SA 8:16"}, "Joab the son of Zeruiah was over the army, Jehoshaphat the son of Ahilud was recorder,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "2SA 8:17"}, "Zadok the son of Ahitub and Ahimelech the son of Abiathar were priests, Seraiah was scribe,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "2SA 8:18"}, "Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was over the Cherethites and the Pelethites, and Dawood\u2019s sons were chief ministers.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "9", "sid": "2SA 9"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "2SA 9:1"}, "Dawood said, \u201cIs there yet any who is left of Saul\u2019s house, that I may show him kindness for Jonathan\u2019s sake?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "2SA 9:2"}, "There was of Saul\u2019s house a servant whose name was Ziba, and they called him to Dawood; and the king said to him, \u201cAre you\nZiba?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cI am your servant.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "2SA 9:3"}, "The king said, \u201cIs there not yet any of Saul\u2019s house, that I may show the kindness of Allah to him?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Ziba said to the king, \u201cJonathan still has a son, who is lame in his feet.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "2SA 9:4"}, "The king said to him, \u201cWhere is he?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Ziba said to the king, \u201cBehold, he is in the house of Machir the son of Ammiel, in Lo Debar.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "2SA 9:5"}, "Then king Dawood sent, and brought him out of the house of Machir the son of Ammiel, from Lo Debar.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "2SA 9:6"}, "Mephibosheth, the son of Jonathan, the son of Saul, came to Dawood, and fell on his face, and showed respect. Dawood said,\n\u201cMephibosheth.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He answered, \u201cBehold, your servant!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "2SA 9:7"}, "Dawood said to him, \u201cDon\u2019t be afraid; for I will surely show you kindness for Jonathan your father\u2019s sake, and will\nrestore to you all the land of Saul your father. You will eat bread at my table continually.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "2SA 9:8"}, "He bowed down, and said, \u201cWhat is your servant, that you should look at such a dead dog as I am?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "2SA 9:9"}, "Then the king called to Ziba, Saul\u2019s servant, and said to him, \u201cAll that belonged to Saul and to all his house I have\ngiven to your master\u2019s son. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "2SA 9:10"}, "Till the land for him, you, your sons, and your servants. Bring in the harvest, that your master\u2019s son may have bread to\neat; but Mephibosheth your master\u2019s son will always eat bread at my table.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Now Ziba had fifteen sons and twenty servants. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "2SA 9:11"}, "Then Ziba said to the king, \u201cAccording to all that my lord the king commands his servant, so your servant will do.\u201d So\nMephibosheth ate at the king\u2019s table, like one of the king\u2019s sons.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "2SA 9:12"}, "Mephibosheth had a young son, whose name was Mica. All that lived in Ziba\u2019s house were servants to Mephibosheth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "2SA 9:13"}, "So Mephibosheth lived in Jerusalem; for he ate continually at the king\u2019s table. He was lame in both his feet.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "10", "sid": "2SA 10"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "2SA 10:1"}, "After this, the king of the children of Ammon died, and Hanun his son reigned in his place.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "2SA 10:2"}, "Dawood said, \u201cI will show kindness to Hanun the son of Nahash, as his father showed kindness to me.\u201d So Dawood sent by his\nservants to comfort him concerning his father. Dawood\u2019s servants came into the land of the children of Ammon.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "2SA 10:3"}, "But the princes of the children of Ammon said to Hanun their lord, \u201cDo you think that Dawood honours your father, in that\nhe has sent comforters to you? Hasn\u2019t Dawood sent his servants to you to search the city, to spy it out, and to overthrow it?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "2SA 10:4"}, "So Hanun took Dawood\u2019s servants, shaved off one half of their beards, and cut off their garments in the middle, even to\ntheir buttocks, and sent them away. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "2SA 10:5"}, "When they told Dawood this, he sent to meet them, for the men were greatly ashamed. The king said, \u201cWait at Jericho until\nyour beards have grown, and then return.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "2SA 10:6"}, "When the children of Ammon saw that they had become odious to Dawood, the children of Ammon sent and hired the Syrians of\nBeth Rehob, and the Syrians of Zobah, twenty thousand footmen, and the king of Maacah with one thousand men, and the men of Tob\ntwelve thousand men. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "2SA 10:7"}, "When Dawood heard of it, he sent Joab, and all the army of the mighty men.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "2SA 10:8"}, "The children of Ammon came out, and put the battle in array at the entrance of the gate. The Syrians of Zobah and of\nRehob, and the men of Tob and Maacah, were by themselves in the field.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "2SA 10:9"}, "Now when Joab saw that the battle was set against him before and behind, he chose of all the choice men of Israel, and put\nthem in array against the Syrians. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "2SA 10:10"}, "The rest of the people he committed into the hand of Abishai his brother; and he put them in array against the children\nof Ammon. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "2SA 10:11"}, "He said, \u201cIf the Syrians are too strong for me, then you shall help me; but if the children of Ammon are too strong for\nyou, then I will come and help you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "2SA 10:12"}, "Be courageous, and let\u2019s be strong for our people, and for the cities of our Allah; and may the LORD do what seems good\nto him.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "2SA 10:13"}, "So Joab and the people who were with him came near to the battle against the Syrians, and they fled before him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "2SA 10:14"}, "When the children of Ammon saw that the Syrians had fled, they likewise fled before Abishai, and entered into the city.\nThen Joab returned from the children of Ammon, and came to Jerusalem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "2SA 10:15"}, "When the Syrians saw that they were defeated by Israel, they gathered themselves together.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "2SA 10:16"}, "Hadadezer sent, and brought out the Syrians who were beyond the River: and they came to Helam, with Shobach the captain\nof the army of Hadadezer at their head. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "2SA 10:17"}, "Dawood was told that; and he gathered all Israel together, passed over the Jordan, and came to Helam. The Syrians set\nthemselves in array against Dawood, and fought with him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "2SA 10:18"}, "The Syrians fled before Israel; and Dawood killed seven hundred charioteers of the Syrians, and forty thousand horsemen,\nand struck Shobach the captain of their army, so that he died there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "2SA 10:19"}, "When all the kings who were servants to Hadadezer saw that they were defeated before Israel, they made peace with Israel,\nand served them. So the Syrians were afraid to help the children of Ammon any more.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "11", "sid": "2SA 11"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "2SA 11:1"}, "At the return of the year, at the time when kings go out, Dawood sent Joab, and his servants with him, and all Israel; and\nthey destroyed the children of Ammon, and besieged Rabbah. But Dawood stayed at Jerusalem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "2SA 11:2"}, "At evening, Dawood arose from his bed and walked on the roof of the king\u2019s house. From the roof, he saw a woman bathing,\nand the woman was very beautiful to look at. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "2SA 11:3"}, "Dawood sent and enquired after the woman. One said, \u201cIsn\u2019t this Bathsheba, the daughter of Eliam, Uriah the Hittite\u2019s\nwife?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "2SA 11:4"}, "Dawood sent messengers, and took her; and she came in to him, and he lay with her (for she was purified from her\nuncleanness); and she returned to her house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "2SA 11:5"}, "The woman conceived; and she sent and told Dawood, and said, \u201cI am with child.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "2SA 11:6"}, "Dawood sent to Joab, \u201cSend me Uriah the Hittite.\u201d Joab sent Uriah to Dawood.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "2SA 11:7"}, "When Uriah had come to him, Dawood asked him how Joab did, and how the people fared, and how the war prospered.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "2SA 11:8"}, "Dawood said to Uriah, \u201cGo down to your house and wash your feet.\u201d Uriah departed out of the king\u2019s house, and a gift from\nthe king was sent after him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "2SA 11:9"}, "But Uriah slept at the door of the king\u2019s house with all the servants of his lord, and didn\u2019t go down to his house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "2SA 11:10"}, "When they had told Dawood, saying, \u201cUriah didn\u2019t go down to his house,\u201d Dawood said to Uriah, \u201cHaven\u2019t you come from a\njourney? Why didn\u2019t you go down to your house?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "2SA 11:11"}, "Uriah said to Dawood, \u201cThe ark, Israel, and Judah, are staying in tents; and my lord Joab and the servants of my lord,\nare encamped in the open field. Shall I then go into my house to eat and to drink, and to lie with my wife? As you live, and as\nyour soul lives, I will not do this thing!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "2SA 11:12"}, "Dawood said to Uriah, \u201cStay here today also, and tomorrow I will let you depart.\u201d So Uriah stayed in Jerusalem that day,\nand the next day. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "2SA 11:13"}, "When Dawood had called him, he ate and drank before him; and he made him drunk. At evening, he went out to lie on his bed\nwith the servants of his lord, but didn\u2019t go down to his house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "2SA 11:14"}, "In the morning, Dawood wrote a letter to Joab, and sent it by the hand of Uriah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "2SA 11:15"}, "He wrote in the letter, saying, \u201cSend Uriah to the forefront of the hottest battle, and retreat from him, that he may be\nstruck, and die.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "2SA 11:16"}, "When Joab kept watch on the city, he assigned Uriah to the place where he knew that valiant men were.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "2SA 11:17"}, "The men of the city went out, and fought with Joab. Some of the people fell, even of Dawood\u2019s servants; and Uriah the\nHittite died also. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "2SA 11:18"}, "Then Joab sent and told Dawood all the things concerning the war;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "2SA 11:19"}, "and he commanded the messenger, saying, \u201cWhen you have finished telling all the things concerning the war to the king,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "2SA 11:20"}, "it shall be that, if the king\u2019s wrath arise, and he asks you, \u2018Why did you go so near to the city to fight? Didn\u2019t you\nknow that they would shoot from the wall? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "2SA 11:21"}, "Who struck Abimelech the son of Jerubbesheth? Didn\u2019t a woman cast an upper millstone on him from the wall, so that he\ndied at Thebez? Why did you go so near the wall?\u2019 then you shall say, \u2018Your servant Uriah the Hittite is also dead.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "2SA 11:22"}, "So the messenger went, and came and showed Dawood all that Joab had sent him for.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "2SA 11:23"}, "The messenger said to Dawood, \u201cThe men prevailed against us, and came out to us into the field, and we were on them even\nto the entrance of the gate. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "2SA 11:24"}, "The shooters shot at your servants from off the wall; and some of the king\u2019s servants are dead, and your servant Uriah\nthe Hittite is also dead.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "2SA 11:25"}, "Then Dawood said to the messenger, \u201cTell Joab, \u2018Don\u2019t let this thing displease you, for the sword devours one as well as\nanother. Make your battle stronger against the city, and overthrow it.\u2019 Encourage him.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "2SA 11:26"}, "When Uriah\u2019s wife heard that Uriah her husband was dead, she mourned for her husband.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "2SA 11:27"}, "When the mourning was past, Dawood sent and took her home to his house, and she became his wife, and bore him a son. But\nthe thing that Dawood had done displeased the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "12", "sid": "2SA 12"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "2SA 12:1"}, "The LORD sent Nathan to Dawood. He came to him, and said to him, \u201cThere were two men in one city; the one rich, and the\nother poor. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "2SA 12:2"}, "The rich man had very many flocks and herds, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "2SA 12:3"}, "but the poor man had nothing, except one little ewe lamb, which he had bought and raised. It grew up together with him,\nand with his children. It ate of his own food, drank of his own cup, and lay in his bosom, and was like a daughter to him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "2SA 12:4"}, "A traveller came to the rich man, and he spared to take of his own flock and of his own herd, to prepare for the wayfaring\nman who had come to him, but took the poor man\u2019s lamb, and prepared it for the man who had come to him.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "2SA 12:5"}, "Dawood\u2019s anger burnt hot against the man, and he said to Nathan, \u201cAs the LORD lives, the man who has done this deserves to\ndie! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "2SA 12:6"}, "He must restore the lamb fourfold, because he did this thing, and because he had no pity!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "2SA 12:7"}, "Nathan said to Dawood, \u201cYou are the man. This is what the LORD, Allah of Israel, says: \u2018I anointed you king over Israel,\nand I delivered you out of the hand of Saul. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "2SA 12:8"}, "I gave you your master\u2019s house, and your master\u2019s wives into your bosom, and gave you the house of Israel and of Judah;\nand if that would have been too little, I would have added to you many more such things.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "2SA 12:9"}, "Why have you despised the LORD\u2019s word, to do that which is evil in his sight? You have struck Uriah the Hittite with the\nsword, and have taken his wife to be your wife, and have slain him with the sword of the children of Ammon.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "2SA 12:10"}, "Now therefore the sword will never depart from your house, because you have despised me, and have taken Uriah the\nHittite\u2019s wife to be your wife.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "2SA 12:11"}, "\u201cThis is what the LORD says: \u2018Behold, I will raise up evil against you out of your own house; and I will take your wives\nbefore your eyes, and give them to your neighbour, and he will lie with your wives in the sight of this sun.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "2SA 12:12"}, "For you did this secretly, but I will do this thing before all Israel, and before the sun.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "2SA 12:13"}, "Dawood said to Nathan, \u201cI have sinned against the LORD.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Nathan said to Dawood, \u201cThe LORD also has put away your sin. You will not die.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "2SA 12:14"}, "However, because by this deed you have given great occasion to the LORD\u2019s enemies to blaspheme, the child also who is\nborn to you will surely die.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "2SA 12:15"}, "Nathan departed to his house. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The LORD struck the child that Uriah\u2019s wife bore to Dawood, and it was very sick.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "2SA 12:16"}, "Dawood therefore begged Allah for the child; and Dawood fasted, and went in, and lay all night on the ground.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "2SA 12:17"}, "The elders of his house arose beside him, to raise him up from the earth: but he would not, and he didn\u2019t eat bread with\nthem. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "2SA 12:18"}, "On the seventh day, the child died. Dawood\u2019s servants were afraid to tell him that the child was dead, for they said,\n\u201cBehold, while the child was yet alive, we spoke to him, and he didn\u2019t listen to our voice. How will he then harm himself, if\nwe tell him that the child is dead?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "2SA 12:19"}, "But when Dawood saw that his servants were whispering together, Dawood perceived that the child was dead; and Dawood said\nto his servants, \u201cIs the child dead?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They said, \u201cHe is dead.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "2SA 12:20"}, "Then Dawood arose from the earth, and washed, and anointed himself, and changed his clothing; and he came into the LORD\u2019s\nhouse, and worshipped. Then he came to his own house; and when he requested, they set bread before him, and he ate.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "2SA 12:21"}, "Then his servants said to him, \u201cWhat is this that you have done? You fasted and wept for the child while he was alive,\nbut when the child was dead, you rose up and ate bread.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "2SA 12:22"}, "He said, \u201cWhile the child was yet alive, I fasted and wept; for I said, \u2018Who knows whether the LORD will not be gracious\nto me, that the child may live?\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "2SA 12:23"}, "But now he is dead, why should I fast? Can I bring him back again? I will go to him, but he will not return to me.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "2SA 12:24"}, "Dawood comforted Bathsheba his wife, and went in to her, and lay with her. She bore a son, and he called his name\nSulaiman. The LORD loved him; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "2SA 12:25"}, "and he sent by the hand of Nathan the prophet, and he named him\nJedidiah,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["12:25 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cJedidiah\u201d means \u201cloved by Yahweh\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " for the LORD\u2019s sake.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "2SA 12:26"}, "Now Joab fought against Rabbah of the children of Ammon, and took the royal city.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "2SA 12:27"}, "Joab sent messengers to Dawood, and said, \u201cI have fought against Rabbah. Yes, I have taken the city of waters.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "2SA 12:28"}, "Now therefore gather the rest of the people together, and encamp against the city, and take it; lest I take the city, and\nit be called by my name.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "2SA 12:29"}, "Dawood gathered all the people together, and went to Rabbah, and fought against it, and took it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "2SA 12:30"}, "He took the crown of their king from off his head; and its weight was a\ntalent", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["12:30 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A talent is about 30 kilograms or 66 pounds or 965 Troy\nounces"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of gold, and in it were precious stones; and it was set on Dawood\u2019s head. He brought a great quantity of plunder out\nof the city. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "2SA 12:31"}, "He brought out the people who were in it, and put them under saws, under iron picks, under axes of iron, and made them\npass through the brick kiln; and he did so to all the cities of the children of Ammon. Then Dawood and all the people returned\nto Jerusalem. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "13", "sid": "2SA 13"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "2SA 13:1"}, "After this, Absalom the son of Dawood had a beautiful sister, whose name was Tamar; and Amnon the son of Dawood loved her.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "2SA 13:2"}, "Amnon was so troubled that he became sick because of his sister Tamar; for she was a virgin; and it seemed hard to Amnon\nto do anything to her. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "2SA 13:3"}, "But Amnon had a friend, whose name was Jonadab, the son of Shimeah, Dawood\u2019s brother; and Jonadab was a very subtle man.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "2SA 13:4"}, "He said to him, \u201cWhy, son of the king, are you so sad from day to day? Won\u2019t you tell me?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Amnon said to him, \u201cI love Tamar, my brother Absalom\u2019s sister.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "2SA 13:5"}, "Jonadab said to him, \u201cLay down on your bed, and pretend to be sick. When your father comes to see you, tell him, \u2018Please\nlet my sister Tamar come and give me bread to eat, and prepare the food in my sight, that I may see it, and eat it from her\nhand.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "2SA 13:6"}, "So Amnon lay down and faked being sick. When the king came to see him, Amnon said to the king, \u201cPlease let my sister Tamar\ncome, and make me a couple of cakes in my sight, that I may eat from her hand.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "2SA 13:7"}, "Then Dawood sent home to Tamar, saying, \u201cGo now to your brother Amnon\u2019s house, and prepare food for him.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "2SA 13:8"}, "So Tamar went to her brother Amnon\u2019s house; and he was lying down. She took dough, and kneaded it, made cakes in his\nsight, and baked the cakes. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "2SA 13:9"}, "She took the pan, and poured them out before him; but he refused to eat. Amnon said, \u201cHave all men leave me.\u201d Then every\nman went out from him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "2SA 13:10"}, "Amnon said to Tamar, \u201cBring the food into the room, that I may eat from your hand.\u201d Tamar took the cakes which she had\nmade, and brought them into the room to Amnon her brother. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "2SA 13:11"}, "When she had brought them near to him to eat, he took hold of her, and said to her, \u201cCome, lie with me, my sister!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "2SA 13:12"}, "She answered him, \u201cNo, my brother, do not force me! For no such thing ought to be done in Israel. Don\u2019t you do this\nfolly. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "2SA 13:13"}, "As for me, where would I carry my shame? And as for you, you will be as one of the fools in Israel. Now therefore, please\nspeak to the king; for he will not withhold me from you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "2SA 13:14"}, "However he would not listen to her voice; but being stronger than she, he forced her, and lay with her.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "2SA 13:15"}, "Then Amnon hated her with exceedingly great hatred; for the hatred with which he hated her was greater than the love with\nwhich he had loved her. Amnon said to her, \u201cArise, be gone!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "2SA 13:16"}, "She said to him, \u201cNot so, because this great wrong in sending me away is worse than the other that you did to me!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["But he would not listen to her. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "2SA 13:17"}, "Then he called his servant who ministered to him, and said, \u201cNow put this woman out from me, and bolt the door after\nher.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "2SA 13:18"}, "She had a garment of various colours on her; for the king\u2019s daughters who were virgins dressed in such robes. Then his\nservant brought her out and bolted the door after her. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "2SA 13:19"}, "Tamar put ashes on her head, and tore her garment of various colours that was on her; and she laid her hand on her head,\nand went her way, crying aloud as she went. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "2SA 13:20"}, "Absalom her brother said to her, \u201cHas Amnon your brother been with you? But now hold your peace, my sister. He is your\nbrother. Don\u2019t take this thing to heart.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["So Tamar remained desolate in her brother Absalom\u2019s house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "2SA 13:21"}, "But when king Dawood heard of all these things, he was very angry.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "2SA 13:22"}, "Absalom spoke to Amnon neither good nor bad; for Absalom hated Amnon, because he had forced his sister Tamar.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "2SA 13:23"}, "After two full years, Absalom had sheep shearers in Baal Hazor, which is beside Ephraim: and Absalom invited all the\nking\u2019s sons. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "2SA 13:24"}, "Absalom came to the king, and said, \u201cSee now, your servant has sheep shearers. Please let the king and his servants go\nwith your servant.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "2SA 13:25"}, "The king said to Absalom, \u201cNo, my son, let\u2019s not all go, lest we be burdensome to you.\u201d He pressed him; however he would\nnot go, but blessed him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "2SA 13:26"}, "Then Absalom said, \u201cIf not, please let my brother Amnon go with us.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The king said to him, \u201cWhy should he go with you?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "2SA 13:27"}, "But Absalom pressed him, and he let Amnon and all the king\u2019s sons go with him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "2SA 13:28"}, "Absalom commanded his servants, saying, \u201cMarqus now, when Amnon\u2019s heart is merry with wine; and when I tell you, \u2018Strike\nAmnon,\u2019 then kill him. Don\u2019t be afraid. Haven\u2019t I commanded you? Be courageous, and be valiant!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "2SA 13:29"}, "The servants of Absalom did to Amnon as Absalom had commanded. Then all the king\u2019s sons arose, and every man got up on\nhis mule, and fled. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "2SA 13:30"}, "While they were on the way, the news came to Dawood, saying, \u201cAbsalom has slain all the king\u2019s sons, and there is not one\nof them left!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "2SA 13:31"}, "Then the king arose, and tore his garments, and lay on the earth; and all his servants stood by with their clothes torn.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "2SA 13:32"}, "Jonadab, the son of Shimeah, Dawood\u2019s brother, answered, \u201cDon\u2019t let my lord suppose that they have killed all the young\nmen the king\u2019s sons; for Amnon only is dead; for by the appointment of Absalom this has been determined from the day that he\nforced his sister Tamar. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "2SA 13:33"}, "Now therefore don\u2019t let my lord the king take the thing to his heart, to think that all the king\u2019s sons are dead; for\nonly Amnon is dead.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "2SA 13:34"}, "But Absalom fled. The young man who kept the watch lifted up his eyes, and looked, and behold, many people were coming by\nway of the hillside behind him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "2SA 13:35"}, "Jonadab said to the king, \u201cBehold, the king\u2019s sons are coming! It is as your servant said.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "2SA 13:36"}, "As soon as he had finished speaking, behold, the king\u2019s sons came, and lifted up their voice, and wept. The king also and\nall his servants wept bitterly. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "2SA 13:37"}, "But Absalom fled, and went to Talmai the son of Ammihur, king of Geshur. Dawood mourned for his son every day.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "2SA 13:38"}, "So Absalom fled, and went to Geshur, and was there three years.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "2SA 13:39"}, "King Dawood longed to go out to Absalom; for he was comforted concerning Amnon, since he was dead.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "14", "sid": "2SA 14"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "2SA 14:1"}, "Now Joab the son of Zeruiah perceived that the king\u2019s heart was towards Absalom.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "2SA 14:2"}, "Joab sent to Tekoa, and brought a wise woman from there, and said to her, \u201cPlease act like a mourner, and put on mourning\nclothing, please, and don\u2019t anoint yourself with oil, but be as a woman who has mourned a long time for the dead.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "2SA 14:3"}, "Go in to the king, and speak like this to him.\u201d So Joab put the words in her mouth.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "2SA 14:4"}, "When the woman of Tekoa spoke to the king, she fell on her face to the ground, showed respect, and said, \u201cHelp, O king!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "2SA 14:5"}, "The king said to her, \u201cWhat ails you?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["She answered, \u201cTruly I am a widow, and my husband is dead. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "2SA 14:6"}, "Your servant had two sons, and they both fought together in the field, and there was no one to part them, but the one\nstruck the other, and killed him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "2SA 14:7"}, "Behold, the whole family has risen against your servant, and they say, \u2018Deliver him who struck his brother, that we may\nkill him for the life of his brother whom he killed, and so destroy the heir also.\u2019 Thus they would quench my coal which is\nleft, and would leave to my husband neither name nor remainder on the surface of the earth.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "2SA 14:8"}, "The king said to the woman, \u201cGo to your house, and I will give a command concerning you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "2SA 14:9"}, "The woman of Tekoa said to the king, \u201cMy lord, O king, may the iniquity be on me, and on my father\u2019s house; and may the\nking and his throne be guiltless.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "2SA 14:10"}, "The king said, \u201cWhoever says anything to you, bring him to me, and he will not bother you any more.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "2SA 14:11"}, "Then she said, \u201cPlease let the king remember Allah your LORD, that the avenger of blood destroy not any more, lest they\ndestroy my son.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cAs the LORD lives, not one hair of your son shall fall to the earth.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "2SA 14:12"}, "Then the woman said, \u201cPlease let your servant speak a word to my lord the king.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cSay on.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "2SA 14:13"}, "The woman said, \u201cWhy then have you devised such a thing against the people of Allah? For in speaking this word the king\nis as one who is guilty, in that the king does not bring home again his banished one.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "2SA 14:14"}, "For we must die, and are like water spilled on the ground, which can\u2019t be gathered up again; neither does Allah take away\nlife, but devises means, that he who is banished not be an outcast from him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "2SA 14:15"}, "Now therefore seeing that I have come to speak this word to my lord the king, it is because the people have made me\nafraid. Your servant said, \u2018I will now speak to the king; it may be that the king will perform the request of his servant.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "2SA 14:16"}, "For the king will hear, to deliver his servant out of the hand of the man who would destroy me and my son together out of\nthe inheritance of Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "2SA 14:17"}, "Then your servant said, \u2018Please let the word of my lord the king bring rest; for as an angel of Allah, so is my lord the\nking to discern good and bad. May the LORD, your Allah, be with you.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "2SA 14:18"}, "Then the king answered the woman, \u201cPlease don\u2019t hide anything from me that I ask you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The woman said, \u201cLet my lord the king now speak.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "2SA 14:19"}, "The king said, \u201cIs the hand of Joab with you in all this?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The woman answered, \u201cAs your soul lives, my lord the king, no one can turn to the right hand or to the left from anything\nthat my lord the king has spoken; for your servant Joab urged me, and he put all these words in the mouth of your servant.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "2SA 14:20"}, "Your servant Joab has done this thing to change the face of the matter. My lord is wise, according to the wisdom of an\nangel of Allah, to know all things that are in the earth.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "2SA 14:21"}, "The king said to Joab, \u201cBehold now, I have done this thing. Go therefore, and bring the young man Absalom back.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "2SA 14:22"}, "Joab fell to the ground on his face, showed respect, and blessed the king. Joab said, \u201cToday your servant knows that I\nhave found favour in your sight, my lord, king, in that the king has performed the request of his servant.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "2SA 14:23"}, "So Joab arose and went to Geshur, and brought Absalom to Jerusalem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "2SA 14:24"}, "The king said, \u201cLet him return to his own house, but let him not see my face.\u201d So Absalom returned to his own house, and\ndidn\u2019t see the king\u2019s face. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "2SA 14:25"}, "Now in all Israel there was no one to be so much praised as Absalom for his beauty. From the sole of his foot even to the\ncrown of his head there was no defect in him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "2SA 14:26"}, "When he cut the hair of his head (now it was at every year\u2019s end that he cut it; because it was heavy on him, therefore\nhe cut it); he weighed the hair of his head at two hundred shekels,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["14:26 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.35 ounces, so 200 shekels is about 2 kilograms or about 4.4\npounds."]}], "caller": "+"}, " after the king\u2019s weight. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "2SA 14:27"}, "Three sons were born to Absalom, and one daughter, whose name was Tamar. She was a woman with a beautiful face.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "2SA 14:28"}, "Absalom lived two full years in Jerusalem, and he didn\u2019t see the king\u2019s face.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "2SA 14:29"}, "Then Absalom sent for Joab, to send him to the king, but he would not come to him. Then he sent again a second time, but\nhe would not come. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "2SA 14:30"}, "Therefore he said to his servants, \u201cBehold, Joab\u2019s field is near mine, and he has barley there. Go and set it on fire.\u201d\nSo Absalom\u2019s servants set the field on fire. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "2SA 14:31"}, "Then Joab arose, and came to Absalom to his house, and said to him, \u201cWhy have your servants set my field on fire?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "2SA 14:32"}, "Absalom answered Joab, \u201cBehold, I sent to you, saying, \u2018Come here, that I may send you to the king, to say, \u201cWhy have I\ncome from Geshur? It would be better for me to be there still. Now therefore let me see the king\u2019s face, and if there is\niniquity in me, let him kill me.\u201d\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "2SA 14:33"}, "So Joab came to the king, and told him; and when he had called for Absalom, he came to the king, and bowed himself on his\nface to the ground before the king; and the king kissed Absalom.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "15", "sid": "2SA 15"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "2SA 15:1"}, "After this, Absalom prepared a chariot and horses for himself, and fifty men to run before him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "2SA 15:2"}, "Absalom rose up early, and stood beside the way of the gate. When any man had a suit which should come to the king for\njudgement, then Absalom called to him, and said, \u201cWhat city are you from?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cYour servant is of one of the tribes of Israel.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "2SA 15:3"}, "Absalom said to him, \u201cBehold, your matters are good and right; but there is no man deputized by the king to hear you.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "2SA 15:4"}, "Absalom said moreover, \u201cOh that I were made judge in the land, that every man who has any suit or cause might come to me,\nand I would do him justice!\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "2SA 15:5"}, "It was so, that when any man came near to bow down to him, he stretched out his hand, and took hold of him, and kissed\nhim. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "2SA 15:6"}, "Absalom did this sort of thing to all Israel who came to the king for judgement. So Absalom stole the hearts of the men of\nIsrael. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "2SA 15:7"}, "At the end of forty years, Absalom said to the king, \u201cPlease let me go and pay my vow, which I have vowed to the LORD, in\nHebron. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "2SA 15:8"}, "For your servant vowed a vow while I stayed at Geshur in Syria, saying, \u2018If the LORD shall indeed bring me again to\nJerusalem, then I will serve the LORD.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "2SA 15:9"}, "The king said to him, \u201cGo in peace.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["So he arose, and went to Hebron. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "2SA 15:10"}, "But Absalom sent spies throughout all the tribes of Israel, saying, \u201cAs soon as you hear the sound of the trumpet, then\nyou shall say, \u2018Absalom is king in Hebron!\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "2SA 15:11"}, "Two hundred men went with Absalom out of Jerusalem, who were invited, and went in their simplicity; and they didn\u2019t know\nanything. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "2SA 15:12"}, "Absalom sent for Ahithophel the Gilonite, Dawood\u2019s counsellor, from his city, even from Giloh, while he was offering the\nsacrifices. The conspiracy was strong; for the people increased continually with Absalom.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "2SA 15:13"}, "A messenger came to Dawood, saying, \u201cThe hearts of the men of Israel are after Absalom.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "2SA 15:14"}, "Dawood said to all his servants who were with him at Jerusalem, \u201cArise! Let\u2019s flee; or else none of us will escape from\nAbsalom. Hurry to depart, lest he overtake us quickly, and bring down evil on us, and strike the city with the edge of the\nsword.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "2SA 15:15"}, "The king\u2019s servants said to the king, \u201cBehold, your servants are ready to do whatever my lord the king chooses.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "2SA 15:16"}, "The king went out, and all his household after him. The king left ten women, who were concubines, to keep the house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "2SA 15:17"}, "The king went out, and all the people after him; and they stayed in Beth Merhak.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "2SA 15:18"}, "All his servants passed on beside him; and all the Cherethites, and all the Pelethites, and all the Gittites, six hundred\nmen who came after him from Gath, passed on before the king. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "2SA 15:19"}, "Then the king said to Ittai the Gittite, \u201cWhy do you also go with us? Return, and stay with the king; for you are a\nforeigner, and also an exile. Return to your own place. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "2SA 15:20"}, "Whereas you came but yesterday, should I today make you go up and down with us, since I go where I may? Return, and take\nback your brothers. Mercy and truth be with you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "2SA 15:21"}, "Ittai answered the king, and said, \u201cAs the LORD lives, and as my lord the king lives, surely in what place my lord the\nking is, whether for death or for life, your servant will be there also.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "2SA 15:22"}, "Dawood said to Ittai, \u201cGo and pass over.\u201d Ittai the Gittite passed over, and all his men, and all the little ones who\nwere with him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "2SA 15:23"}, "All the country wept with a loud voice, and all the people passed over. The king also himself passed over the brook\nKidron, and all the people passed over, towards the way of the wilderness.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "2SA 15:24"}, "Behold, Zadok also came, and all the Levites with him, bearing the ark of the covenant of Allah; and they set down\nAllah\u2019s ark; and Abiathar went up, until all the people finished passing out of the city.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "2SA 15:25"}, "The king said to Zadok, \u201cCarry Allah\u2019s ark back into the city. If I find favour in the LORD\u2019s eyes, he will bring me\nagain, and show me both it, and his habitation; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "2SA 15:26"}, "but if he says, \u2018I have no delight in you;\u2019 behold, here I am. Let him do to me as seems good to him.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "2SA 15:27"}, "The king said also to Zadok the priest, \u201cAren\u2019t you a seer? Return into the city in peace, and your two sons with you,\nAhimaaz your son, and Jonathan the son of Abiathar. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "2SA 15:28"}, "Behold, I will stay at the fords of the wilderness, until word comes from you to inform me.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "2SA 15:29"}, "Zadok therefore and Abiathar carried Allah\u2019s ark to Jerusalem again; and they stayed there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "2SA 15:30"}, "Dawood went up by the ascent of the Mount of Olives, and wept as he went up; and he had his head covered, and went\nbarefoot. All the people who were with him each covered his head, and they went up, weeping as they went up.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "2SA 15:31"}, "Someone told Dawood, saying, \u201cAhithophel is amongst the conspirators with Absalom.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Dawood said, \u201cLORD, please turn the counsel of Ahithophel into foolishness.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "2SA 15:32"}, "When Dawood had come to the top, where Allah was worshipped, behold, Hushai the Archite came to meet him with his tunic\ntorn, and earth on his head. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "2SA 15:33"}, "Dawood said to him, \u201cIf you pass on with me, then you will be a burden to me;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "2SA 15:34"}, "but if you return to the city, and tell Absalom, \u2018I will be your servant, O king. As I have been your father\u2019s servant in\ntime past, so I will now be your servant; then will you defeat for me the counsel of Ahithophel.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "2SA 15:35"}, "Don\u2019t you have Zadok and Abiathar the priests there with you? Therefore whatever you hear out of the king\u2019s house, tell\nit to Zadok and Abiathar the priests. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "2SA 15:36"}, "Behold, they have there with them their two sons, Ahimaaz, Zadok\u2019s son, and Jonathan, Abiathar\u2019s son. Send to me\neverything that you shall hear by them.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "2SA 15:37"}, "So Hushai, Dawood\u2019s friend, came into the city; and Absalom came into Jerusalem.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "16", "sid": "2SA 16"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "2SA 16:1"}, "When Dawood was a little past the top, behold, Ziba the servant of Mephibosheth met him with a couple of donkeys saddled,\nand on them two hundred loaves of bread, and one hundred clusters of raisins, and one hundred summer fruits, and a container of\nwine. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "2SA 16:2"}, "The king said to Ziba, \u201cWhat do you mean by these?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Ziba said, \u201cThe donkeys are for the king\u2019s household to ride on; and the bread and summer fruit for the young men to eat;\nand the wine, that those who are faint in the wilderness may drink.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "2SA 16:3"}, "The king said, \u201cWhere is your master\u2019s son?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Ziba said to the king, \u201cBehold, he is staying in Jerusalem; for he said, \u2018Today the house of Israel will restore me the\nkingdom of my father.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "2SA 16:4"}, "Then the king said to Ziba, \u201cBehold, all that belongs to Mephibosheth is yours.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Ziba said, \u201cI bow down. Let me find favour in your sight, my lord, O king.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "2SA 16:5"}, "When king Dawood came to Bahurim, behold, a man of the family of Saul\u2019s house came out, whose name was Shimei, the son of\nGera. He came out and cursed as he came. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "2SA 16:6"}, "He cast stones at Dawood, and at all the servants of king Dawood, and all the people and all the mighty men were on his\nright hand and on his left. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "2SA 16:7"}, "Shimei said when he cursed, \u201cBe gone, be gone, you man of blood, and wicked fellow!\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "2SA 16:8"}, "The LORD has returned on you all the blood of Saul\u2019s house, in whose place you have reigned! The LORD has delivered the\nkingdom into the hand of Absalom your son! Behold, you are caught by your own mischief, because you are a man of blood!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "2SA 16:9"}, "Then Abishai the son of Zeruiah said to the king, \u201cWhy should this dead dog curse my lord the king? Please let me go over\nand take off his head.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "2SA 16:10"}, "The king said, \u201cWhat have I to do with you, you sons of Zeruiah? Because he curses, and because the LORD has said to him,\n\u2018Curse Dawood;\u2019 who then shall say, \u2018Why have you done so?\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "2SA 16:11"}, "Dawood said to Abishai, and to all his servants, \u201cBehold, my son, who came out of my bowels, seeks my life. How much more\nthis Benjamite, now? Leave him alone, and let him curse; for the LORD has invited him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "2SA 16:12"}, "It may be that the LORD will look on the wrong done to me, and that the LORD will repay me good for the cursing of me\ntoday.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "2SA 16:13"}, "So Dawood and his men went by the way; and Shimei went along on the hillside opposite him, and cursed as he went, threw\nstones at him, and threw dust. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "2SA 16:14"}, "The king, and all the people who were with him, came weary; and he refreshed himself there.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "2SA 16:15"}, "Absalom and all the people, the men of Israel, came to Jerusalem, and Ahithophel with him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "2SA 16:16"}, "When Hushai the Archite, Dawood\u2019s friend, had come to Absalom, Hushai said to Absalom, \u201cLong live the king! Long live the\nking!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "2SA 16:17"}, "Absalom said to Hushai, \u201cIs this your kindness to your friend? Why didn\u2019t you go with your friend?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "2SA 16:18"}, "Hushai said to Absalom, \u201cNo; but whomever the LORD, and this people, and all the men of Israel have chosen, I will be\nhis, and I will stay with him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "2SA 16:19"}, "Again, whom should I serve? Shouldn\u2019t I serve in the presence of his son? As I have served in your father\u2019s presence, so\nI will be in your presence.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "2SA 16:20"}, "Then Absalom said to Ahithophel, \u201cGive your counsel what we shall do.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "2SA 16:21"}, "Ahithophel said to Absalom, \u201cGo in to your father\u2019s concubines that he has left to keep the house. Then all Israel will\nhear that you are abhorred by your father. Then the hands of all who are with you will be strong.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "2SA 16:22"}, "So they spread a tent for Absalom on the top of the house, and Absalom went in to his father\u2019s concubines in the sight of\nall Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "2SA 16:23"}, "The counsel of Ahithophel, which he gave in those days, was as if a man enquired at the inner sanctuary of Allah. All the\ncounsel of Ahithophel both was like this with Dawood and with Absalom.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "17", "sid": "2SA 17"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "2SA 17:1"}, "Moreover Ahithophel said to Absalom, \u201cLet me now choose twelve thousand men, and I will arise and pursue after Dawood\ntonight. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "2SA 17:2"}, "I will come on him while he is weary and exhausted, and will make him afraid. All the people who are with him will flee. I\nwill strike the king only, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "2SA 17:3"}, "and I will bring back all the people to you. The man whom you seek is as if all returned. All the people shall be in\npeace.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "2SA 17:4"}, "The saying pleased Absalom well, and all the elders of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "2SA 17:5"}, "Then Absalom said, \u201cNow call Hushai the Archite also, and let\u2019s hear likewise what he says.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "2SA 17:6"}, "When Hushai had come to Absalom, Absalom spoke to him, saying, \u201cAhithophel has spoken like this. Shall we do what he says?\nIf not, speak up.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "2SA 17:7"}, "Hushai said to Absalom, \u201cThe counsel that Ahithophel has given this time is not good.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "2SA 17:8"}, "Hushai said moreover, \u201cYou know your father and his men, that they are mighty men, and they are fierce in their minds,\nlike a bear robbed of her cubs in the field. Your father is a man of war, and will not lodge with the people.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "2SA 17:9"}, "Behold, he is now hidden in some pit, or in some other place. It will happen, when some of them have fallen at the first,\nthat whoever hears it will say, \u2018There is a slaughter amongst the people who follow Absalom!\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "2SA 17:10"}, "Even he who is valiant, whose heart is as the heart of a lion, will utterly melt; for all Israel knows that your father\nis a mighty man, and those who are with him are valiant men. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "2SA 17:11"}, "But I counsel that all Israel be gathered together to you, from Dan even to Beersheba, as the sand that is by the sea for\nmultitude; and that you go to battle in your own person. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "2SA 17:12"}, "So we will come on him in some place where he will be found, and we will light on him as the dew falls on the ground,\nthen we will not leave so much as one of him and of all the men who are with him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "2SA 17:13"}, "Moreover, if he has gone into a city, then all Israel will bring ropes to that city, and we will draw it into the river,\nuntil there isn\u2019t one small stone found there.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "2SA 17:14"}, "Absalom and all the men of Israel said, \u201cThe counsel of Hushai the Archite is better than the counsel of Ahithophel.\u201d For\nthe LORD had ordained to defeat the good counsel of Ahithophel, to the intent that the LORD might bring evil on Absalom.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "2SA 17:15"}, "Then Hushai said to Zadok and to Abiathar the priests, \u201cAhithophel counselled Absalom and the elders of Israel that way;\nand I have counselled this way. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "2SA 17:16"}, "Now therefore send quickly, and tell Dawood, saying, \u2018Don\u2019t lodge tonight at the fords of the wilderness, but by all\nmeans pass over; lest the king be swallowed up, and all the people who are with him.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "2SA 17:17"}, "Now Jonathan and Ahimaaz were staying by En Rogel; and a female servant used to go and tell them; and they went and told\nking Dawood. For they might not be seen to come into the city. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "2SA 17:18"}, "But a boy saw them, and told Absalom. Then they both went away quickly, and came to the house of a man in Bahurim, who\nhad a well in his court; and they went down there. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "2SA 17:19"}, "The woman took and spread the covering over the well\u2019s mouth, and spread out crushed grain on it; and nothing was known.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "2SA 17:20"}, "Absalom\u2019s servants came to the woman to the house; and they said, \u201cWhere are Ahimaaz and Jonathan?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The woman said to them, \u201cThey have gone over the brook of water.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["When they had sought and could not find them, they returned to Jerusalem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "2SA 17:21"}, "After they had departed, they came up out of the well, and went and told king Dawood; and they said to Dawood, \u201cArise and\npass quickly over the water; for thus has Ahithophel counselled against you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "2SA 17:22"}, "Then Dawood arose, and all the people who were with him, and they passed over the Jordan. By the morning light there\nlacked not one of them who had not gone over the Jordan. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "2SA 17:23"}, "When Ahithophel saw that his counsel was not followed, he saddled his donkey, arose, and went home, to his city, and set\nhis house in order, and hanged himself; and he died, and was buried in the tomb of his father.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "2SA 17:24"}, "Then Dawood came to Mahanaim. Absalom passed over the Jordan, he and all the men of Israel with him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "2SA 17:25"}, "Absalom set Amasa over the army instead of Joab. Now Amasa was the son of a man whose name was Ithra the Israelite, who\nwent in to Abigail the daughter of Nahash, sister to Zeruiah, Joab\u2019s mother.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "2SA 17:26"}, "Israel and Absalom encamped in the land of Gilead. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "2SA 17:27"}, "When Dawood had come to Mahanaim, Shobi the son of Nahash of Rabbah of the children of Ammon, and Machir the son of\nAmmiel of Lodebar, and Barzillai the Gileadite of Rogelim, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "2SA 17:28"}, "brought beds, basins, earthen vessels, wheat, barley, meal, parched grain, beans, lentils, roasted grain,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "2SA 17:29"}, "honey, butter, sheep, and cheese of the herd, for Dawood, and for the people who were with him, to eat; for they said,\n\u201cThe people are hungry, weary, and thirsty in the wilderness.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "18", "sid": "2SA 18"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "2SA 18:1"}, "Dawood counted the people who were with him, and set captains of thousands and captains of hundreds over them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "2SA 18:2"}, "Dawood sent the people out, a third part under the hand of Joab, and a third part under the hand of Abishai the son of\nZeruiah, Joab\u2019s brother, and a third part under the hand of Ittai the Gittite. The king said to the people, \u201cI will also surely\ngo out with you myself.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "2SA 18:3"}, "But the people said, \u201cYou shall not go out; for if we flee away, they will not care for us; neither if half of us die,\nwill they care for us. But you are worth ten thousand of us. Therefore now it is better that you are ready to help us out of\nthe city.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "2SA 18:4"}, "The king said to them, \u201cI will do what seems best to you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The king stood beside the gate, and all the people went out by hundreds and by thousands.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "2SA 18:5"}, "The king commanded Joab and Abishai and Ittai, saying, \u201cDeal gently for my sake with the young man, even with Absalom.\u201d\nAll the people heard when the king commanded all the captains concerning Absalom.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "2SA 18:6"}, "So the people went out into the field against Israel; and the battle was in the forest of Ephraim.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "2SA 18:7"}, "The people of Israel were struck there before Dawood\u2019s servants, and there was a great slaughter there that day of twenty\nthousand men. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "2SA 18:8"}, "For the battle was there spread over the surface of all the country, and the forest devoured more people that day than the\nsword devoured. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "2SA 18:9"}, "Absalom happened to meet Dawood\u2019s servants. Absalom was riding on his mule, and the mule went under the thick boughs of a\ngreat oak, and his head caught hold of the oak, and he was taken up between the sky and earth; and the mule that was under him\nwent on. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "2SA 18:10"}, "A certain man saw it, and told Joab, and said, \u201cBehold, I saw Absalom hanging in an oak.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "2SA 18:11"}, "Joab said to the man who told him, \u201cBehold, you saw it, and why didn\u2019t you strike him there to the ground? I would have\ngiven you ten pieces of silver, and a sash.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "2SA 18:12"}, "The man said to Joab, \u201cThough I should receive a thousand pieces of silver in my hand, I still wouldn\u2019t stretch out my\nhand against the king\u2019s son; for in our hearing the king commanded you and Abishai and Ittai, saying, \u2018Beware that no one touch\nthe young man Absalom.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "2SA 18:13"}, "Otherwise if I had dealt falsely against his life (and there is no matter hidden from the king), then you yourself would\nhave set yourself against me.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "2SA 18:14"}, "Then Joab said, \u201cI\u2019m not going to wait like this with you.\u201d He took three darts in his hand, and thrust them through the\nheart of Absalom, while he was yet alive in the middle of the oak.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "2SA 18:15"}, "Ten young men who bore Joab\u2019s armour surrounded and struck Absalom, and killed him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "2SA 18:16"}, "Joab blew the trumpet, and the people returned from pursuing after Israel; for Joab held the people back.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "2SA 18:17"}, "They took Absalom and cast him into a great pit in the forest, and raised over him a very great heap of stones. Then all\nIsrael fled, each to his own tent. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "2SA 18:18"}, "Now Absalom in his lifetime had taken and reared up for himself the pillar which is in the king\u2019s valley, for he said, \u201cI\nhave no son to keep my name in memory.\u201d He called the pillar after his own name. It is called Absalom\u2019s monument, to this day.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "2SA 18:19"}, "Then Ahimaaz the son of Zadok said, \u201cLet me now run and carry the king news, how the LORD has avenged him of his\nenemies.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "2SA 18:20"}, "Joab said to him, \u201cYou must not be the bearer of news today, but you must carry news another day. But today you must\ncarry no news, because the king\u2019s son is dead.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "2SA 18:21"}, "Then Joab said to the Cushite, \u201cGo, tell the king what you have seen!\u201d The Cushite bowed himself to Joab, and ran.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "2SA 18:22"}, "Then Ahimaaz the son of Zadok said yet again to Joab, \u201cBut come what may, please let me also run after the Cushite.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Joab said, \u201cWhy do you want to run, my son, since you will have no reward for the news?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "2SA 18:23"}, "\u201cBut come what may,\u201d he said, \u201cI will run.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said to him, \u201cRun!\u201d Then Ahimaaz ran by the way of the Plain, and outran the Cushite.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "2SA 18:24"}, "Now Dawood was sitting between the two gates; and the watchman went up to the roof of the gate to the wall, and lifted up\nhis eyes, and looked, and, behold, a man running alone. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "2SA 18:25"}, "The watchman cried, and told the king. The king said, \u201cIf he is alone, there is news in his mouth.\u201d He came closer and\ncloser. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "2SA 18:26"}, "The watchman saw another man running; and the watchman called to the gatekeeper, and said, \u201cBehold, a man running alone!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The king said, \u201cHe also brings news.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "2SA 18:27"}, "The watchman said, \u201cI think the running of the first one is like the running of Ahimaaz the son of Zadok.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The king said, \u201cHe is a good man, and comes with good news.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "2SA 18:28"}, "Ahimaaz called, and said to the king, \u201cAll is well.\u201d He bowed himself before the king with his face to the earth, and\nsaid, \u201cBlessed is Allah your LORD, who has delivered up the men who lifted up their hand against my lord the king!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "2SA 18:29"}, "The king said, \u201cIs it well with the young man Absalom?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Ahimaaz answered, \u201cWhen Joab sent the king\u2019s servant, even me your servant, I saw a great tumult, but I don\u2019t know what it\nwas.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "2SA 18:30"}, "The king said, \u201cCome and stand here.\u201d He came, and stood still.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "2SA 18:31"}, "Behold, the Cushite came. The Cushite said, \u201cNews for my lord the king, for the LORD has avenged you today of all those\nwho rose up against you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "2SA 18:32"}, "The king said to the Cushite, \u201cIs it well with the young man Absalom?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The Cushite answered, \u201cMay the enemies of my lord the king, and all who rise up against you to do you harm, be as that young\nman is.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "2SA 18:33"}, "The king was much moved, and went up to the room over the gate, and wept. As he went, he said, \u201cMy son Absalom! My son,\nmy son Absalom! I wish I had died for you, Absalom, my son, my son!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "19", "sid": "2SA 19"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "2SA 19:1"}, "Joab was told, \u201cBehold, the king weeps and mourns for Absalom.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "2SA 19:2"}, "The victory that day was turned into mourning amongst all the people; for the people heard it said that day, \u201cThe king\ngrieves for his son.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "2SA 19:3"}, "The people sneaked into the city that day, as people who are ashamed steal away when they flee in battle.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "2SA 19:4"}, "The king covered his face, and the king cried with a loud voice, \u201cMy son Absalom, Absalom, my son, my son!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "2SA 19:5"}, "Joab came into the house to the king, and said, \u201cToday you have shamed the faces of all your servants, who today have\nsaved your life, and the lives of your sons and of your daughters, and the lives of your wives, and the lives of your\nconcubines; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "2SA 19:6"}, "in that you love those who hate you, and hate those who love you. For you have declared today that princes and servants\nare nothing to you. For today I perceive that if Absalom had lived, and all we had died today, then it would have pleased you\nwell. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "2SA 19:7"}, "Now therefore arise, go out, and speak to comfort your servants; for I swear by the LORD, if you don\u2019t go out, not a man\nwill stay with you this night. That would be worse to you than all the evil that has happened to you from your youth until\nnow.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "2SA 19:8"}, "Then the king arose, and sat in the gate. They told to all the people, saying, \u201cBehold, the king is sitting in the gate.\u201d\nAll the people came before the king. Now Israel had fled every man to his tent.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "2SA 19:9"}, "All the people were at strife throughout all the tribes of Israel, saying, \u201cThe king delivered us out of the hand of our\nenemies, and he saved us out of the hand of the Philistines; and now he has fled out of the land from Absalom.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "2SA 19:10"}, "Absalom, whom we anointed over us, is dead in battle. Now therefore why don\u2019t you speak a word of bringing the king\nback?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "2SA 19:11"}, "King Dawood sent to Zadok and to Abiathar the priests, saying, \u201cSpeak to the elders of Judah, saying, \u2018Why are you the\nlast to bring the king back to his house? Since the speech of all Israel has come to the king, to return him to his house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "2SA 19:12"}, "You are my brothers. You are my bone and my flesh. Why then are you the last to bring back the king?\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "2SA 19:13"}, "Say to Amasa, \u2018Aren\u2019t you my bone and my flesh? Allah do so to me, and more also, if you aren\u2019t captain of the army\nbefore me continually instead of Joab.\u2019\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "2SA 19:14"}, "He bowed the heart of all the men of Judah, even as one man; so that they sent to the king, saying, \u201cReturn, you and all\nyour servants.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "2SA 19:15"}, "So the king returned, and came to the Jordan. Judah came to Gilgal, to go to meet the king, to bring the king over the\nJordan. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "2SA 19:16"}, "Shimei the son of Gera, the Benjamite, who was of Bahurim, hurried and came down with the men of Judah to meet king\nDawood. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "2SA 19:17"}, "There were a thousand men of Benjamin with him, and Ziba the servant of Saul\u2019s house, and his fifteen sons and his twenty\nservants with him; and they went through the Jordan in the presence of the king.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "2SA 19:18"}, "A ferry boat went to bring over the king\u2019s household, and to do what he thought good. Shimei the son of Gera fell down\nbefore the king, when he had come over the Jordan. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "2SA 19:19"}, "He said to the king, \u201cDon\u2019t let my lord impute iniquity to me, or remember that which your servant did perversely the day\nthat my lord the king went out of Jerusalem, that the king should take it to his heart.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "2SA 19:20"}, "For your servant knows that I have sinned. Therefore behold, I have come today as the first of all the house of Yusuf to\ngo down to meet my lord the king.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "2SA 19:21"}, "But Abishai the son of Zeruiah answered, \u201cShouldn\u2019t Shimei be put to death for this, because he cursed the LORD\u2019s\nanointed?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "2SA 19:22"}, "Dawood said, \u201cWhat have I to do with you, you sons of Zeruiah, that you should be adversaries to me today? Shall any man\nbe put to death today in Israel? For don\u2019t I know that I am king over Israel today?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "2SA 19:23"}, "The king said to Shimei, \u201cYou will not die.\u201d The king swore to him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "2SA 19:24"}, "Mephibosheth the son of Saul came down to meet the king; and he had neither groomed his feet, nor trimmed his beard, nor\nwashed his clothes, from the day the king departed until the day he came home in peace.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "2SA 19:25"}, "When he had come to Jerusalem to meet the king, the king said to him, \u201cWhy didn\u2019t you go with me, Mephibosheth?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "2SA 19:26"}, "He answered, \u201cMy lord, O king, my servant deceived me. For your servant said, \u2018I will saddle a donkey for myself, that I\nmay ride on it and go with the king,\u2019 because your servant is lame.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "2SA 19:27"}, "He has slandered your servant to my lord the king, but my lord the king is as an angel of Allah. Therefore do what is\ngood in your eyes. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "2SA 19:28"}, "For all my father\u2019s house were but dead men before my lord the king; yet you set your servant amongst those who ate at\nyour own table. What right therefore have I yet that I should cry any more to the king?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "2SA 19:29"}, "The king said to him, \u201cWhy do you speak any more of your matters? I say, you and Ziba divide the land.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "2SA 19:30"}, "Mephibosheth said to the king, \u201cYes, let him take all, because my lord the king has come in peace to his own house.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "2SA 19:31"}, "Barzillai the Gileadite came down from Rogelim; and he went over the Jordan with the king, to conduct him over the\nJordan. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "2SA 19:32"}, "Now Barzillai was a very aged man, even eighty years old. He had provided the king with sustenance while he stayed at\nMahanaim; for he was a very great man. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "2SA 19:33"}, "The king said to Barzillai, \u201cCome over with me, and I will sustain you with me in Jerusalem.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "2SA 19:34"}, "Barzillai said to the king, \u201cHow many are the days of the years of my life, that I should go up with the king to\nJerusalem? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "2SA 19:35"}, "I am eighty years old, today. Can I discern between good and bad? Can your servant taste what I eat or what I drink? Can\nI hear the voice of singing men and singing women any more? Why then should your servant be a burden to my lord the king?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "2SA 19:36"}, "Your servant would but just go over the Jordan with the king. Why should the king repay me with such a reward?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "2SA 19:37"}, "Please let your servant turn back again, that I may die in my own city, by the grave of my father and my mother. But\nbehold, your servant Chimham; let him go over with my lord the king; and do to him what shall seem good to you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "2SA 19:38"}, "The king answered, \u201cChimham shall go over with me, and I will do to him that which shall seem good to you. Whatever you\nrequest of me, that I will do for you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "2SA 19:39"}, "All the people went over the Jordan, and the king went over. Then the king kissed Barzillai, and blessed him; and he\nreturned to his own place. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "2SA 19:40"}, "So the king went over to Gilgal, and Chimham went over with him. All the people of Judah brought the king over, and also\nhalf the people of Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "2SA 19:41"}, "Behold, all the men of Israel came to the king, and said to the king, \u201cWhy have our brothers the men of Judah stolen you\naway, and brought the king, and his household, over the Jordan, and all Dawood\u2019s men with him?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "2SA 19:42"}, "All the men of Judah answered the men of Israel, \u201cBecause the king is a close relative to us. Why then are you angry\nabout this matter? Have we eaten at all at the king\u2019s cost? Or has he given us any gift?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "2SA 19:43"}, "The men of Israel answered the men of Judah, and said, \u201cWe have ten parts in the king, and we have also more claim to\nDawood than you. Why then did you despise us, that our advice should not be first had in bringing back our king?\u201d The words of\nthe men of Judah were fiercer than the words of the men of Israel.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "20", "sid": "2SA 20"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "2SA 20:1"}, "There happened to be there a wicked fellow, whose name was Sheba, the son of Bichri, a Benjamite; and he blew the trumpet,\nand said, \u201cWe have no portion in Dawood, neither have we inheritance in the son of Jesse. Every man to his tents, Israel!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "2SA 20:2"}, "So all the men of Israel went up from following Dawood, and followed Sheba the son of Bichri; but the men of Judah joined\nwith their king, from the Jordan even to Jerusalem. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "2SA 20:3"}, "Dawood came to his house at Jerusalem; and the king took the ten women his concubines, whom he had left to keep the house,\nand put them in custody, and provided them with sustenance, but didn\u2019t go in to them. So they were shut up to the day of their\ndeath, living in widowhood. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "2SA 20:4"}, "Then the king said to Amasa, \u201cCall me the men of Judah together within three days, and be here present.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "2SA 20:5"}, "So Amasa went to call the men of Judah together; but he stayed longer than the set time which he had appointed him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "2SA 20:6"}, "Dawood said to Abishai, \u201cNow Sheba the son of Bichri will do us more harm than Absalom did. Take your lord\u2019s servants, and\npursue after him, lest he get himself fortified cities, and escape out of our sight.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "2SA 20:7"}, "Joab\u2019s men went out after him, and the Cherethites and the Pelethites, and all the mighty men; and they went out of\nJerusalem, to pursue Sheba the son of Bichri. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "2SA 20:8"}, "When they were at the great stone which is in Gibeon, Amasa came to meet them. Joab was clothed in his apparel of war that\nhe had put on, and on it was a sash with a sword fastened on his waist in its sheath; and as he went along it fell out.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "2SA 20:9"}, "Joab said to Amasa, \u201cIs it well with you, my brother?\u201d Joab took Amasa by the beard with his right hand to kiss him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "2SA 20:10"}, "But Amasa took no heed to the sword that was in Joab\u2019s hand. So he struck him with it in the body, and shed out his\nbowels to the ground, and didn\u2019t strike him again; and he died. Joab and Abishai his brother pursued Sheba the son of Bichri.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "2SA 20:11"}, "One of Joab\u2019s young men stood by him, and said, \u201cHe who favours Joab, and he who is for Dawood, let him follow Joab!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "2SA 20:12"}, "Amasa lay wallowing in his blood in the middle of the highway. When the man saw that all the people stood still, he\ncarried Amasa out of the highway into the field, and cast a garment over him, when he saw that everyone who came by him stood\nstill. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "2SA 20:13"}, "When he was removed out of the highway, all the people went on after Joab, to pursue Sheba the son of Bichri.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "2SA 20:14"}, "He went through all the tribes of Israel to Habil, and to Beth Maacah, and all the Berites. They were gathered together,\nand went also after him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "2SA 20:15"}, "They came and besieged him in Habil of Beth Maacah, and they cast up a mound against the city, and it stood against the\nrampart; and all the people who were with Joab battered the wall, to throw it down.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "2SA 20:16"}, "Then a wise woman cried out of the city, \u201cHear, hear! Please say to Joab, \u2018Come near here, that I may speak with you.\u2019\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "2SA 20:17"}, "He came near to her; and the woman said, \u201cAre you Joab?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He answered, \u201cI am.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Then she said to him, \u201cHear the words of your servant.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He answered, \u201cI\u2019m listening.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "2SA 20:18"}, "Then she spoke, saying, \u201cThey used to say in old times, \u2018They shall surely ask counsel at Habil;\u2019 and so they settled a\nmatter. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "2SA 20:19"}, "I am amongst those who are peaceable and faithful in Israel. You seek to destroy a city and a mother in Israel. Why will\nyou swallow up the LORD\u2019s inheritance?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "2SA 20:20"}, "Joab answered, \u201cFar be it, far be it from me, that I should swallow up or destroy.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "2SA 20:21"}, "The matter is not so. But a man of the hill country of Ephraim, Sheba the son of Bichri by name, has lifted up his hand\nagainst the king, even against Dawood. Just deliver him, and I will depart from the city.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The woman said to Joab, \u201cBehold, his head will be thrown to you over the wall.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "2SA 20:22"}, "Then the woman went to all the people in her wisdom. They cut off the head of Sheba the son of Bichri, and threw it out\nto Joab. He blew the trumpet, and they were dispersed from the city, every man to his tent. Then Joab returned to Jerusalem to\nthe king. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "2SA 20:23"}, "Now Joab was over all the army of Israel, Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was over the Cherethites and over the Pelethites,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "2SA 20:24"}, "Adoram was over the men subject to forced labour, Jehoshaphat the son of Ahilud was the recorder,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "2SA 20:25"}, "Sheva was scribe, and Zadok and Abiathar were priests, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "2SA 20:26"}, "and Ira the Jairite was chief minister to Dawood. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "21", "sid": "2SA 21"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "2SA 21:1"}, "There was a famine in the days of Dawood for three years, year after year; and Dawood sought the face of the LORD. The\nLORD said, \u201cIt is for Saul, and for his bloody house, because he put the Gibeonites to death.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "2SA 21:2"}, "The king called the Gibeonites, and said to them (now the Gibeonites were not of the children of Israel, but of the\nremnant of the Amorites, and the children of Israel had sworn to them; and Saul sought to kill them in his zeal for the\nchildren of Israel and Judah); \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "2SA 21:3"}, "and Dawood said to the Gibeonites, \u201cWhat should I do for you? And with what should I make atonement, that you may bless\nthe LORD\u2019s inheritance?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "2SA 21:4"}, "The Gibeonites said to him, \u201cIt is no matter of silver or gold between us and Saul, or his house; neither is it for us to\nput any man to death in Israel.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cI will do for you whatever you say.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "2SA 21:5"}, "They said to the king, \u201cThe man who consumed us, and who devised against us, that we should be destroyed from remaining in\nany of the borders of Israel, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "2SA 21:6"}, "let seven men of his sons be delivered to us, and we will hang them up to the LORD in Gibeah of Saul, the chosen of the\nLORD.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The king said, \u201cI will give them.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "2SA 21:7"}, "But the king spared Mephibosheth, the son of Jonathan the son of Saul, because of the LORD\u2019s oath that was between them,\nbetween Dawood and Jonathan the son of Saul. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "2SA 21:8"}, "But the king took the two sons of Rizpah the daughter of Aiah, whom she bore to Saul, Armoni and Mephibosheth; and the\nfive sons of Michal the daughter of Saul, whom she bore to Adriel the son of Barzillai the Meholathite.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "2SA 21:9"}, "He delivered them into the hands of the Gibeonites, and they hanged them on the mountain before the LORD, and all seven of\nthem fell together. They were put to death in the days of harvest, in the first days, at the beginning of barley harvest.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "2SA 21:10"}, "Rizpah the daughter of Aiah took sackcloth, and spread it for herself on the rock, from the beginning of harvest until\nwater poured on them from the sky. She allowed neither the birds of the sky to rest on them by day, nor the animals of the\nfield by night. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "2SA 21:11"}, "Dawood was told what Rizpah the daughter of Aiah, the concubine of Saul, had done.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "2SA 21:12"}, "So Dawood went and took the bones of Saul and the bones of Jonathan his son from the men of Jabesh Gilead, who had stolen\nthem from the street of Beth Shan, where the Philistines had hanged them, in the day that the Philistines killed Saul in\nGilboa; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "2SA 21:13"}, "and he brought up from there the bones of Saul and the bones of Jonathan his son. They also gathered the bones of those\nwho were hanged. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "2SA 21:14"}, "They buried the bones of Saul and Jonathan his son in the country of Benjamin in Zela, in the tomb of Kish his father:\nand they performed all that the king commanded. After that, Allah answered prayer for the land.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "2SA 21:15"}, "The Philistines had war again with Israel; and Dawood went down, and his servants with him, and fought against the\nPhilistines. Dawood grew faint; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "2SA 21:16"}, "and Ishbibenob, who was of the sons of the giant, the weight of whose spear was three hundred shekels of bronze in\nweight, he being armed with a new sword, thought he would kill Dawood.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "2SA 21:17"}, "But Abishai the son of Zeruiah helped him, and struck the Philistine, and killed him. Then the men of Dawood swore to\nhim, saying, \u201cDon\u2019t go out with us to battle any more, so that you don\u2019t quench the lamp of Israel.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "2SA 21:18"}, "After this, there was again war with the Philistines at Gob. Then Sibbecai the Hushathite killed Saph, who was of the\nsons of the giant. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "2SA 21:19"}, "There was again war with the Philistines at Gob; and Elhanan the son of Jaare-Oregim the Bethlehemite killed Goliath the\nGittite\u2019s brother, the staff of whose spear was like a weaver\u2019s beam.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "2SA 21:20"}, "There was again war at Gath, where there was a man of great stature, who had six fingers on every hand, and six toes on\nevery foot, twenty four in count; and he also was born to the giant.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "2SA 21:21"}, "When he defied Israel, Jonathan the son of Shimei, Dawood\u2019s brother, killed him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "2SA 21:22"}, "These four were born to the giant in Gath; and they fell by the hand of Dawood, and by the hand of his servants.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "22", "sid": "2SA 22"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "2SA 22:1"}, "Dawood spoke to the LORD the words of this song in the day that the LORD delivered him out of the hand of all his enemies,\nand out of the hand of Saul, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "2SA 22:2"}, "and he said: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cThe LORD is my rock, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["my fortress, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and my deliverer, even mine; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "2SA 22:3"}, "Allah is my rock in whom I take refuge; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["my shield, and the horn of my salvation, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["my high tower, and my refuge. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["My saviour, you save me from violence. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "2SA 22:4"}, "I call on the LORD, who is worthy to be praised; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["So shall I be saved from my enemies. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "2SA 22:5"}, "For the waves of death surrounded me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The floods of ungodliness made me afraid. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "2SA 22:6"}, "The cords of Sheol", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["22:6 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Sheol is the place of the\ndead."]}], "caller": "+"}, " were around me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The snares of death caught me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "2SA 22:7"}, "In my distress, I called on the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Yes, I called to my Allah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He heard my voice out of his temple. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["My cry came into his ears. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "2SA 22:8"}, "Then the earth shook and trembled. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The foundations of heaven quaked and were shaken, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["because he was angry. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "2SA 22:9"}, "Smoke went up out of his nostrils. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Consuming fire came out of his mouth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Coals were kindled by it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "2SA 22:10"}, "He bowed the heavens also, and came down. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Thick darkness was under his feet. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "2SA 22:11"}, "He rode on a cherub, and flew. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Yes, he was seen on the wings of the wind. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "2SA 22:12"}, "He made darkness a shelter around himself: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["gathering of waters, and thick clouds of the skies. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "2SA 22:13"}, "At the brightness before him, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["coals of fire were kindled. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "2SA 22:14"}, "The LORD thundered from heaven. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The Most High uttered his voice. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "2SA 22:15"}, "He sent out arrows, and scattered them; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["lightning, and confused them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "2SA 22:16"}, "Then the channels of the sea appeared. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The foundations of the world were laid bare by the LORD\u2019s rebuke,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["at the blast of the breath of his nostrils. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "2SA 22:17"}, "He sent from on high and he took me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He drew me out of many waters. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "2SA 22:18"}, "He delivered me from my strong enemy, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["from those who hated me, for they were too mighty for me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "2SA 22:19"}, "They came on me in the day of my calamity, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but the LORD was my support. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "2SA 22:20"}, "He also brought me out into a large place. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He delivered me, because he delighted in me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "2SA 22:21"}, "The LORD rewarded me according to my righteousness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He rewarded me according to the cleanness of my hands. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "2SA 22:22"}, "For I have kept the LORD\u2019s ways, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and have not wickedly departed from my Allah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "2SA 22:23"}, "For all his ordinances were before me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["As for his statutes, I didn\u2019t depart from them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "2SA 22:24"}, "I was also perfect towards him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I kept myself from my iniquity. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "2SA 22:25"}, "Therefore the LORD has rewarded me according to my righteousness,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["According to my cleanness in his eyesight. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "2SA 22:26"}, "With the merciful you will show yourself merciful. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["With the perfect man you will show yourself perfect. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "2SA 22:27"}, "With the pure you will show yourself pure. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["With the crooked you will show yourself shrewd. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "2SA 22:28"}, "You will save the afflicted people, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["But your eyes are on the arrogant, that you may bring them down.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "2SA 22:29"}, "For you are my lamp, LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The LORD will light up my darkness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "2SA 22:30"}, "For by you, I run against a troop. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["By my Allah, I leap over a wall. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "2SA 22:31"}, "As for Allah, his way is perfect. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The LORD\u2019s word is tested. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He is a shield to all those who take refuge in him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "2SA 22:32"}, "For who is Allah, besides the LORD? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Who is a rock, besides our Allah? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "2SA 22:33"}, "Allah is my strong fortress. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He makes my way perfect. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "2SA 22:34"}, "He makes his feet like hinds\u2019 feet, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and sets me on my high places. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "2SA 22:35"}, "He teaches my hands to war, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["so that my arms bend a bow of bronze. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "2SA 22:36"}, "You have also given me the shield of your salvation. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Your gentleness has made me great. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "2SA 22:37"}, "You have enlarged my steps under me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["My feet have not slipped. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "2SA 22:38"}, "I have pursued my enemies and destroyed them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I didn\u2019t turn again until they were consumed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "2SA 22:39"}, "I have consumed them, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and struck them through, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["so that they can\u2019t arise. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Yes, they have fallen under my feet. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "2SA 22:40"}, "For you have armed me with strength for the battle. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You have subdued under me those who rose up against me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "2SA 22:41"}, "You have also made my enemies turn their backs to me, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that I might cut off those who hate me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "2SA 22:42"}, "They looked, but there was no one to save; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["even to the LORD, but he didn\u2019t answer them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "2SA 22:43"}, "Then I beat them as small as the dust of the earth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I crushed them as the mire of the streets, and spread them abroad.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "2SA 22:44"}, "You also have delivered me from the strivings of my people.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You have kept me to be the head of the nations. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["A people whom I have not known will serve me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "2SA 22:45"}, "The foreigners will submit themselves to me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["As soon as they hear of me, they will obey me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "2SA 22:46"}, "The foreigners will fade away, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and will come trembling out of their close places. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "2SA 22:47"}, "The LORD lives! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Blessed be my rock! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Exalted be Allah, the rock of my salvation, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "2SA 22:48"}, "even Allah who executes vengeance for me, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who brings down peoples under me, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "2SA 22:49"}, "who brings me away from my enemies. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Yes, you lift me up above those who rise up against me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You deliver me from the violent man. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "2SA 22:50"}, "Therefore I will give thanks to you, LORD, amongst the nations,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and will sing praises to your name. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "2SA 22:51"}, "He gives great deliverance to his king, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and shows loving kindness to his anointed, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to Dawood and to his offspring, forever more.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "23", "sid": "2SA 23"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "2SA 23:1"}, "Now these are the last words of Dawood. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Dawood the son of Jesse says, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the man who was raised on high says, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the anointed of Allah of Yaqub, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the sweet psalmist of Israel: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "2SA 23:2"}, "\u201cThe LORD\u2019s Spirit spoke by me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["His word was on my tongue. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "2SA 23:3"}, "The Allah of Israel said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the Rock of Israel spoke to me, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u2018One who rules over men righteously, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who rules in the fear of Allah, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "2SA 23:4"}, "shall be as the light of the morning, when the sun rises, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["a morning without clouds, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["when the tender grass springs out of the earth, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["through clear shining after rain.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "2SA 23:5"}, "Isn\u2019t my house so with Allah? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Yet he has made with me an everlasting covenant, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["ordered in all things, and sure, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for it is all my salvation, and all my desire, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["although he doesn\u2019t make it grow. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "2SA 23:6"}, "But all the ungodly will be as thorns to be thrust away, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["because they can\u2019t be taken with the hand, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "2SA 23:7"}, "But the man who touches them must be armed with iron and the staff of a spear.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They will be utterly burnt with fire in their place.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "2SA 23:8"}, "These are the names of the mighty men whom Dawood had: Josheb Basshebeth a Tahchemonite, chief of the captains; he was\ncalled Adino the Eznite, who killed eight hundred at one time. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "2SA 23:9"}, "After him was Eleazar the son of Dodai the son of an Ahohite, one of the three mighty men with Dawood, when they defied\nthe Philistines who were there gathered together to battle, and the men of Israel had gone away.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "2SA 23:10"}, "He arose and struck the Philistines until his hand was weary, and his hand froze to the sword; and the LORD worked a\ngreat victory that day; and the people returned after him only to take plunder.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "2SA 23:11"}, "After him was Shammah the son of Agee a Hararite. The Philistines had gathered together into a troop, where there was a\nplot of ground full of lentils; and the people fled from the Philistines.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "2SA 23:12"}, "But he stood in the middle of the plot and defended it, and killed the Philistines; and the LORD worked a great victory.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "2SA 23:13"}, "Three of the thirty chief men went down, and came to Dawood in the harvest time to the cave of Adullam; and the troop of\nthe Philistines was encamped in the valley of Rephaim. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "2SA 23:14"}, "Dawood was then in the stronghold; and the garrison of the Philistines was then in Bethlehem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "2SA 23:15"}, "Dawood longed, and said, \u201cOh that someone would give me water to drink from the well of Bethlehem, which is by the gate!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "2SA 23:16"}, "The three mighty men broke through the army of the Philistines, and drew water out of the well of Bethlehem that was by\nthe gate, and took it and brought it to Dawood; but he would not drink of it, but poured it out to the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "2SA 23:17"}, "He said, \u201cBe it far from me, LORD, that I should do this! Isn\u2019t this the blood of the men who risked their lives to go?\u201d\nTherefore he would not drink it. The three mighty men did these things.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "2SA 23:18"}, "Abishai, the brother of Joab, the son of Zeruiah, was chief of the three. He lifted up his spear against three hundred\nand killed them, and had a name amongst the three. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "2SA 23:19"}, "Wasn\u2019t he most honourable of the three? Therefore he was made their captain. However he wasn\u2019t included as one of the\nthree. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "2SA 23:20"}, "Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, the son of a valiant man of Kabzeel, who had done mighty deeds, killed the two sons of Ariel\nof Moab. He also went down and killed a lion in the middle of a pit in a time of snow.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "2SA 23:21"}, "He killed a huge Egyptian, and the Egyptian had a spear in his hand; but he went down to him with a staff, and plucked\nthe spear out of the Egyptian\u2019s hand, and killed him with his own spear.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "2SA 23:22"}, "Benaiah the son of Jehoiada did these things, and had a name amongst the three mighty men.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "2SA 23:23"}, "He was more honourable than the thirty, but he didn\u2019t attain to the three. Dawood set him over his guard.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "2SA 23:24"}, "Asahel the brother of Joab was one of the thirty: Elhanan the son of Dodo of Bethlehem,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "2SA 23:25"}, "Shammah the Harodite, Elika the Harodite, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "2SA 23:26"}, "Helez the Paltite, Ira the son of Ikkesh the Tekoite, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "2SA 23:27"}, "Abiezer the Anathothite, Mebunnai the Hushathite, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "2SA 23:28"}, "Zalmon the Ahohite, Maharai the Netophathite, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "2SA 23:29"}, "Heleb the son of Baanah the Netophathite, Ittai the son of Ribai of Gibeah of the children of Benjamin,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "2SA 23:30"}, "Benaiah a Pirathonite, Hiddai of the brooks of Gaash. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "2SA 23:31"}, "Abialbon the Arbathite, Azmaveth the Barhumite, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "2SA 23:32"}, "Eliahba the Shaalbonite, the sons of Jashen, Jonathan, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "2SA 23:33"}, "Shammah the Hararite, Ahiam the son of Sharar the Ararite,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "2SA 23:34"}, "Eliphelet the son of Ahasbai, the son of the Maacathite, Eliam the son of Ahithophel the Gilonite,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "2SA 23:35"}, "Hezro the Carmelite, Paarai the Arbite, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "2SA 23:36"}, "Igal the son of Nathan of Zobah, Bani the Gadite, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "2SA 23:37"}, "Zelek the Ammonite, Naharai the Beerothite, armour bearers to Joab the son of Zeruiah,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "2SA 23:38"}, "Ira the Ithrite, Gareb the Ithrite, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "2SA 23:39"}, "and Uriah the Hittite: thirty-seven in all. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "24", "sid": "2SA 24"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "2SA 24:1"}, "Again the LORD\u2019s anger burnt against Israel, and he moved Dawood against them, saying, \u201cGo, count Israel and Judah.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "2SA 24:2"}, "The king said to Joab the captain of the army, who was with him, \u201cNow go back and forth through all the tribes of Israel,\nfrom Dan even to Beersheba, and count the people, that I may know the sum of the people.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "2SA 24:3"}, "Joab said to the king, \u201cNow may Allah your LORD add to the people, however many they may be, one hundred times; and may\nthe eyes of my lord the king see it. But why does my lord the king delight in this thing?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "2SA 24:4"}, "Notwithstanding, the king\u2019s word prevailed against Joab, and against the captains of the army. Joab and the captains of\nthe army went out from the presence of the king to count the people of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "2SA 24:5"}, "They passed over the Jordan, and encamped in Aroer, on the right side of the city that is in the middle of the valley of\nGad, and to Jazer; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "2SA 24:6"}, "then they came to Gilead, and to the land of Tahtim Hodshi; and they came to Dan Jaan, and around to Sidon,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "2SA 24:7"}, "and came to the stronghold of Tyre, and to all the cities of the Hivites, and of the Canaanites; and they went out to the\nsouth of Judah, at Beersheba. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "2SA 24:8"}, "So when they had gone back and forth through all the land, they came to Jerusalem at the end of nine months and twenty\ndays. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "2SA 24:9"}, "Joab gave up the sum of the counting of the people to the king: and there were in Israel eight hundred thousand valiant\nmen who drew the sword; and the men of Judah were five hundred thousand men.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "2SA 24:10"}, "Dawood\u2019s heart struck him after he had counted the people. Dawood said to the LORD, \u201cI have sinned greatly in that which\nI have done. But now, the LORD, put away, I beg you, the iniquity of your servant; for I have done very foolishly.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "2SA 24:11"}, "When Dawood rose up in the morning, the LORD\u2019s word came to the prophet Gad, Dawood\u2019s seer, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "2SA 24:12"}, "\u201cGo and speak to Dawood, \u2018The LORD says, \u201cI offer you three things. Choose one of them, that I may do it to you.\u201d\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "2SA 24:13"}, "So Gad came to Dawood, and told him, and said to him, \u201cShall seven years of famine come to you in your land? Or will you\nflee three months before your foes while they pursue you? Or shall there be three days\u2019 pestilence in your land? Now answer,\nand consider what answer I shall return to him who sent me.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "2SA 24:14"}, "Dawood said to Gad, \u201cI am in distress. Let us fall now into the LORD\u2019s hand; for his mercies are great. Let me not fall\ninto man\u2019s hand.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "2SA 24:15"}, "So the LORD sent a pestilence on Israel from the morning even to the appointed time; and seventy thousand men died of the\npeople from Dan even to Beersheba. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "2SA 24:16"}, "When the angel stretched out his hand towards Jerusalem to destroy it, the LORD relented of the disaster, and said to the\nangel who destroyed the people, \u201cIt is enough. Now withdraw your hand.\u201d The LORD\u2019s angel was by the threshing floor of Araunah\nthe Jebusite. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "2SA 24:17"}, "Dawood spoke to the LORD when he saw the angel who struck the people, and said, \u201cBehold, I have sinned, and I have done\nperversely; but these sheep, what have they done? Please let your hand be against me, and against my father\u2019s house.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "2SA 24:18"}, "Gad came that day to Dawood, and said to him, \u201cGo up, build an altar to the LORD on the threshing floor of Araunah the\nJebusite.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "2SA 24:19"}, "Dawood went up according to the saying of Gad, as the LORD commanded.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "2SA 24:20"}, "Araunah looked out, and saw the king and his servants coming on towards him. Then Araunah went out, and bowed himself\nbefore the king with his face to the ground. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "2SA 24:21"}, "Araunah said, \u201cWhy has my lord the king come to his servant?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Dawood said, \u201cTo buy your threshing floor, to build an altar to the LORD, that the plague may be stopped from afflicting the\npeople.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "2SA 24:22"}, "Araunah said to Dawood, \u201cLet my lord the king take and offer up what seems good to him. Behold, the cattle for the burnt\noffering, and the threshing instruments and the yokes of the oxen for the wood.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "2SA 24:23"}, "All this, O king, does Araunah give to the king.\u201d Araunah said to the king, \u201cMay Allah your LORD accept you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "2SA 24:24"}, "The king said to Araunah, \u201cNo; but I will most certainly buy it from you for a price. I will not offer burnt offerings to\nthe LORD my Allah which cost me nothing.\u201d So Dawood bought the threshing floor and the oxen for fifty\nshekels", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["24:24 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.35 ounces, so 50 shekels is about 0.5 kilograms or 1.1\npounds."]}], "caller": "+"}, " of silver. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "2SA 24:25"}, "Dawood built an altar to the LORD there, and offered burnt offerings and peace offerings. So the LORD was entreated for\nthe land, and the plague was removed from Israel. "]}]}